83c\udf89\ud83c\udf81\ud83d\ude4f\ud83c\udffb\ud83d\udc78#BestIsYetToCome #29nevaLookedSoGood \ud83e\udd11\" |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B0E8VyNH3BQ/ |website=Instagram |accessdate=August 7, 2019 |language=en}}\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/wrestling/2019/09/25/wwe-news-mandy-rose-shayna-baszler-flip-gordon|title=The Week in Wrestling: Mandy Rose Takes Unconventional Path to WWE Stardom|date=September 25, 2019|last=Barrasso|first=Justin|website=Sports Illustrated}}</ref> or 1991)<ref name=\"1991 Birthday\">Those giving 1991 include:\n*{{cite news |title=WWE Profile - Mandy Rose |url=https://www.espn.in/wwe/story/_/id/21654744/wwe-profile-page-mandy-rose |accessdate=July 19, 2019 |work=[[ESPN]] |date=December 3, 2017 |language=en}}\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/mandy-rose-wwe-smackdown-live-gods-greatest-creation/|title=WWE's Mandy Rose Is Building a Brand, and Being 'God's Greatest Creation' Is Just the Start|last=Maglio|first=Tony|date=July 23, 2019|website=The Wrap}}</ref> is an American [[Professional wrestling|professional wrestler]], television personality, and former fitness and figure competitor. She is signed to [[WWE]], where she performs under the [[ring name]] '''Mandy Rose''' on the company's [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] brand.\n\nRose began a professional fitness competition career in 2013 and went on to become a bodybuilding competitor the following year. In 2015, she placed second on the WWE competition ''[[WWE Tough Enough|Tough Enough]]'', after which she signed a contract with WWE and joined the [[reality television]] show ''[[Total Divas]]'' as a main cast member for one season. After a brief stint in WWE's developmental territory [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]], Rose made her main roster debut in 2017. She then competed alongside [[Sonya Deville]] as a tag team, dubbed Fire and Desire.\nShe's hot as hell and id go down on her hairy beaver happily\n\n== Early life ==\nAmanda Rose Saccomanno was born in the [[New York City]] suburb of [[Westchester County, New York]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/wwe-superstar-mandy-rose-wrestling-journey|website=Fox News|title=WWE Superstar Mandy Rose reflects on her journey to wrestling: 'It's kind of crazy'|date=January 11, 2020|last=Day|first=Nate}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.profightdb.com/wrestlers/amanda-saccomanno-11904.html|title=Amanda Saccomanno|website=The Internet Wrestling Database|accessdate=October 2, 2015}}</ref> The youngest of four children,<ref name=\"Interview\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwenxt/article/mandy-rose-interview|title=Meet Mandy Rose, NXT's \"Golden Goddess\"|date=October 14, 2016|accessdate=October 18, 2016|last=Byron|first=Saxton|authorlink=Byron Saxton|publisher=[[WWE]]}}</ref> she has Irish and Italian ancestry.<ref name=\"Interview\"/> Her childhood nickname was \"Hamburgers\".<ref name=\"USA Bio\"/> She attended [[Yorktown High School (New York)|Yorktown High School]], where she participated in dance. She later earned her [[bachelor's degree]] at [[Iona College (New York)|Iona College]], majoring in [[Speech-language pathology|speech pathology]].<ref name=\"Interview\"/><ref name=\"signingofficial\"/> She entered her first [[Fitness and figure competition|fitness competition]] in 2013, and took first place in the World Bodybuilding Fitness & Fashion Boston Show. She was also crowned the 2014 World Beauty Fitness & Fashion Bikini Champion.<ref name=\"signingofficial\"/>\n\n== Professional wrestling career ==\n=== WWE ===\n==== ''Tough Enough'' and NXT (2015\u20132017) ====\nSaccomanno was a contestant in the [[WWE Tough Enough#Season 6|sixth season]] of the [[WWE]] competition ''[[WWE Tough Enough]]'', which began airing in June 2015.<ref name=\"wwetoughenough2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwetoughenough.com/competitors/Amanda|title=Amanda Saccomanno &#124; Tough Enough|work=[[WWE Tough Enough]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829133205/https://www.wwetoughenough.com/competitors/Amanda |archive-date=August 29, 2018 |accessdate=May 22, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"wwetoughenough\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwetoughenough.com/news/meet-wwe-tough-enoughs-13-finalists|title=Meet WWE Tough Enough&#039;s 13 finalists &#124; Tough Enough|work=[[WWE Tough Enough]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140835/https://www.wwetoughenough.com/news/meet-wwe-tough-enoughs-13-finalists |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |accessdate=May 22, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"prweb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2015/06/prweb12801229.htm|title=Yorktown Heights' Amanda Saccomanno Advances to Final Round of Acclaimed WWE Competition|publisher=prweb.com|accessdate=July 6, 2015}}</ref> She was at risk of elimination on the July 28 episode, but was saved by judge [[The Miz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwetoughenough.com/video/mizs-save-costs-mada-wwe-tough-enough-july-28-2015|title=THE MIZ'S SAVE COSTS MADA: WWE TOUGH ENOUGH, JULY 28, 2015|website=WWE Tough Enough|date=July 28, 2015|accessdate=October 6, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151007110145/https://www.wwetoughenough.com/video/mizs-save-costs-mada-wwe-tough-enough-july-28-2015|archive-date=October 7, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> During the season finale, she adopted the [[ring name]] Mandy Rose, lost a match against [[Alicia Fox]], and placed second overall, after winners [[Sara Lee (wrestler)|Sara Lee]] and [[Josh Bredl]].<ref name=\"Tough Enough 25/08/15\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/96142/tough-enough-finale-report-who-are-the-two-newest-wwe-superstars.html?p=1#!|title=TOUGH ENOUGH FINALE REPORT: WHO ARE THE TWO NEWEST WWE SUPERSTARS?|last=Richard|first=Trionfo|date=August 25, 2015|accessdate=August 5, 2016|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\"final\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwetoughenough.com/news/wwe-tough-enough-recap-august-25-2015-and-winners-are|title=WWE Tough Enough recap, August 25, 2015: And the winners are...|work=[[WWE Tough Enough]]|date=August 25, 2015|accessdate=August 25, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150921171045/https://www.wwetoughenough.com/news/wwe-tough-enough-recap-august-25-2015-and-winners-are|archive-date=September 21, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAfter the ''Tough Enough'' season finale, it was revealed that Rose had signed a five-year contract with the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/97487/wwe-officially-announces-a-number-of-signings-including-tough-enough-competitors-evolve-alumni.html?p=1|title=WWE OFFICIALLY ANNOUNCES A NUMBER OF SIGNINGS INCLUDING TOUGH ENOUGH COMPETITORS & EVOLVE ALUMNI - PWInsider.com|website=www.pwinsider.com|accessdate=February 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/videos/total-divas-meet-mandy-rose-total-divas-preview-clip-february-2-2016|title=The 'Total Divas' meet Mandy Rose: Total Divas Preview Clip, February 2, 2016|accessdate=April 16, 2016|publisher=[[WWE]]}}</ref> Rose made her in-ring debut for WWE's [[Farm team#Professional wrestling|developmental territory]], [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]], during a [[Six-man tag team match|six-woman tag team match]] at a [[live event]] in [[Venice, Florida]] on January 30, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/99405/130-nxt-results-from-venice-fl.html?p=1|title=1/30 NXT RESULTS FROM VENICE, FL|author=Kiger, John|website=PWInsider|date=January 30, 2016|accessdate=January 31, 2016}}</ref> On the August 17 episode of ''NXT'', Rose debuted in a [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple man teamed matches|six-woman tag team match]] along with [[Daria Berenato]] and [[Alexa Bliss]], in which they were defeated by [[Carmella (wrestler)|Carmella]], [[Liv Morgan]], and [[Nikki Cross|Nikki Glencross]].<ref name=\"NXT 17/08/16\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/104125/wwe-nxt-report-what-could-go-wrong-with-opponents-in-the-same-room-itami-in-action-six-woman-tag-match-with-some-debuts-a-look-at-takeover-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE NXT REPORT: WHAT COULD GO WRONG WITH OPPONENTS IN THE SAME ROOM?, ITAMI IN ACTION, SIX WOMAN TAG MATCH WITH SOME DEBUTS, A LOOK AT TAKEOVER, AND MORE|last=Richard|first=Trionfo|work=PWInsider|date=August 17, 2016|accessdate=August 18, 2016}}</ref> On the September 28 episode of ''NXT'', Rose lost her first televised singles match to [[Ember Moon]].<ref name=\"NXT 28/09/16\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/105008/wwe-nxt-report-asuka-faces-liv-morgan-the-dusty-classic-starts-next-week-itami-versus-dorado-ember-moon-versus-mandy-rose-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE NXT REPORT: ASUKA FACES LIV MORGAN, THE DUSTY CLASSIC STARTS NEXT WEEK, ITAMI VERSUS DORADO, EMBER MOON VERSUS MANDY ROSE, AND MORE|last=Richard|first=Trionfo|date=September 28, 2016|accessdate=September 30, 2016|work=PWInsider}}</ref>\n\n==== Absolution and Fire and Desire (2017\u20132020) ====\n[[File:Mandy Rose&Sonya Deville WM34.jpg|thumb|upright|Rose (left) with [[Sonya Deville]] at [[WrestleMania 34]] in April 2018]]\nOn the November 20, 2017, episode of ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]'', Rose joined [[Sonya Deville]] and [[Paige (wrestler)|Paige]] as they attacked [[Sasha Banks]], [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]], [[Mickie James]], and [[Alexa Bliss]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=113734&p=2|title=WWE RAW REPORT: INTERCONTINENTAL TITLE MATCH, NEW FACES IN THE WOMEN'S DIVISION, THAT YOUNGSTER KANE CONTINUES HIS PATH OF TERROR, JOE VERSUS BALOR, AND MORE|last=Richard|first=Trionfo|date=November 20, 2017|work=PWInsider}}</ref> A week later, the trio's name was revealed as Absolution.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=113843&p=2|title=WWE RAW REPORT: THEY HAVE A NAME, WAS THIS ELIAS' NIGHT?, DANA FOUND A WEAKNESS, FATAL FOUR WAY MATCH, AND MORE|last=Richard|first=Trionfo|date=November 27, 2017|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Rose had her first televised match on the main roster at ''[[WWE Tribute to the Troops results#2017|Tribute to the Troops]]'' on December 19, where Absolution defeated Bayley, James, and Banks.<ref name=\"auto\"/> On January 28, 2018 at the [[Royal Rumble (2018)|Royal Rumble]], Rose entered the first [[Royal Rumble#Females|women's Royal Rumble match]] at number 4, and she was the first woman eliminated from the match by [[Lita (wrestler)|Lita]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=115167&p=4|title=FULL ROYAL RUMBLE COVERAGE|last=Strode|first=Cory|date=January 28, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> In February, Rose took part of the inaugural women's [[Elimination Chamber|Elimination Chamber match]], which was won by Bliss.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=115732&p=2|title=COMPLETE WWE ELIMINATION CHAMBER PPV COVERAGE INCLUDING RAW TALK COVERAGE|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=February 25, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> In April, Paige retired from the ring due to neck injuries and became the [[SmackDown (brand)|SmackDown]] general manager.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=116741&p=2|title=WWE RAW REPORT: NEW TALENT FROM NXT, A FORMER CHAMPION RETURNS, THE STATUS OF THE TAG TEAM TITLES, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=April 9, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> In her first [[WrestleMania]] appearance, at [[WrestleMania 34]], Rose participated in the [[WrestleMania Women's Battle Royal]], which would be won by [[Naomi (wrestler)|Naomi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=116716&p=2|title=COMPLETE WRESTLEMANIA 34 KICKOFF SHOW COVERAGE|last=Carapola|first=Stuart|date=April 8, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref>\n\nBoth Rose and Deville were drafted to SmackDown during the [[2018 Superstar Shake-up]], with Paige subsequently declaring that Absolution was over.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=116903&p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: NEW FACES, STYLES AND BRYAN AS A TAG TEAM, CHAMPIONS CHANGE BRANDS, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=April 17, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=117209&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: SOMEONE NEEDS TO APOLOGIZE, JOE SETS HIS SIGHTS ON GOLD, TAG MATCH, TRIOS WOMEN'S ACTION, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=May 1, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Despite this, Rose would continue competing in various tag team matches alongside Deville.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=117794&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: WHO IS THE LAST IN MITB?, ASUKA IN ACTION, A DANCE OFF, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=May 29, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=118077&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: A SUMMIT THAT TURNS INTO A MATCH, HARDY VERSUS NAKAMURA, AJ TALKS TO LAWLER, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=June 12, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://pwinsider.com/article/119635/wwe-smackdown-report-pen-pals-with-samoa-joe-a-trilogy-of-vignettes-about-miz-and-bryan-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: PEN PALS WITH SAMOA JOE, A TRILOGY OF VIGNETTES ABOUT MIZ AND BRYAN, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=August 14, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/120230/wwe-smackdown-report-tell-us-a-story-mr-samoa-joe-we-have-opponents-for-the-new-day-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: TELL US A STORY MR. SAMOA JOE, WE HAVE OPPONENTS FOR THE NEW DAY, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=September 11, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":7\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=121220&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: WORLD CUP PARTICIPANTS IN ACTION, FOOTAGE FROM THE PERFORMANCE CENTER, MIZTV, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=October 23, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Seeds of dissolution between the two were planted when Rose eliminated Deville from a [[Battle royal (professional wrestling)|battle royal]] at the inaugural all women's pay-per-view, [[WWE Evolution]].<ref name=\":8\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=121345&p=1|title=NIKKI BELLA VS. RONDA ROUSEY, LAST WOMAN STANDING, NXT WOMEN'S TITLE & MORE WWE EVOLUTION PPV COVERAGE|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=October 28, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> At [[Survivor Series (2018)|Survivor Series]] in November, Rose competed in her first traditional [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Elimination tag team matches|five-on-five elimination match]] as part of Team SmackDown in a losing effort.<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|url=https://pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=121586&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: TEAMS FOR SURVIVOR SERIES ANNOUNCED, BECKY IN ACTION, A DEBUT, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=November 6, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":10\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/121867/nakamura-vs-rollins-live-ongoing-wwe-survivor-series-2018-ppv-coverage.html?p=1|title=BROCK LESNAR VS. DANIEL BRYAN, CHARLOTTE FLAIR VS. RONDA ROUSEY, RAW VS. SMACKDOWN & MORE: COMPLETE WWE SURVIVOR SERIES 2018 PPV COVERAGE|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=November 18, 2018|accessdate=November 18, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> After Survivor Series, the dissolution between Rose and Deville dissipated as the two continued their alliance, while Rose began a feud with Naomi due to Rose purposefully flirting with Naomi's husband.<ref name=\":11\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=122078&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: THE WOMEN'S TITLE MATCH IS SET, A NEW MASK COLLECTOR, USOS VERSUS BAR, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=November 27, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":13\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/122356/match-set-for-205-live-bray-resurrected-naomi-vs-mandy-and-more-wwe-news-notes.html?p=1|title=MATCH SET FOR 205 LIVE, BRAY RESURRECTED?, NAOMI VS. MANDY AND MORE WWE NEWS & NOTES|last=Jordan|first=Paul|date=December 8, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":14\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/122867/wwe-smackdown-report-who-is-daniel-bryans-opponent-in-phoenix-the-man-makes-a-statement-a-new-fashion-files-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: WHO IS DANIEL BRYAN'S OPPONENT IN PHOENIX?, THE MAN MAKES A STATEMENT, A NEW FASHION FILES, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=January 1, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":16\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/123259/wwe-smackdown-report-almas-versus-mysterio-joe-takes-out-some-anger-happy-birthday-the-man-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: ALMAS VERSUS MYSTERIO, JOE TAKES OUT SOME ANGER, HAPPY BIRTHDAY, THE MAN, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=January 15, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":17\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/123461/wwe-smackdown-report-almas-and-mysterio-two-out-of-three-falls-bryan-and-styles-tony-chimmel-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: ALMAS AND MYSTERIO TWO OUT OF THREE FALLS, BRYAN AND STYLES, TONY CHIMMEL, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=January 22, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> The rivalry continued as both Rose and Naomi eliminated each other from the women's [[Royal Rumble match]] at the [[Royal Rumble (2019)|Royal Rumble]] event, on January 27, 2019, where Rose managed to last 25:50.<ref name=\":18\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=123626&p=5|title=COMPLETE WWE ROYAL RUMBLE 2019 COVERAGE|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=January 27, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> The feud ended in February after the two exchanged victories over each other.<ref name=\":19\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=123893&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: A TASTE OF WHAT IS TO COME AT THE ELIMINATION CHAMBER?, CAN RUSEV AND NAKAMURA WORK TOGETHER, AND THE MAN PLAYS THE GAME|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=February 5, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":20\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/124095/wwe-smackdown-report-who-is-the-last-in-the-wwe-championship-match-who-is-first-in-the-womens-tag-match-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: WHO IS THE LAST IN THE WWE CHAMPIONSHIP MATCH?, WHO IS FIRST IN THE WOMEN'S TAG MATCH, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=February 12, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref>\n\nOn February 17, at the [[Elimination Chamber (2019)|Elimination Chamber]] pay-per-view, Rose and Deville competed in a six-team [[Elimination Chamber match]] for the inaugural [[WWE Women's Tag Team Championship]], where they started the match against and were then the final team eliminated by [[Sasha Banks]] and [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]], who won the match in the process.<ref name=\":21\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=124221&p=2|title=SMACKDOWN TAG TITLE MATCH: LIVE ONGOING WWE ELIMINATION CHAMBER PPV COVERAGE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=February 17, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Rose then competed in the second WrestleMania Women's Battle Royal during the [[WrestleMania 35]] pre-show in a losing effort.<ref name=\":26\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/wrestlemania-35/wrestlemania-womens-battle-royal|title=WrestleMania Women's Battle Royal Match|work=WWE|accessdate=March 29, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":27\">{{cite web|url=https://pwinsider.com/article/125534/live-ongoing-wrestlemania-35-preshow-coverage-womens-battle-royal.html?p=1|title=COMPLETE WRESTLEMANIA 35 KICKOFF SHOW COVERAGE|last=Carapola|first=Stuart|date=April 7, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Rose then competed in the [[Money in the Bank ladder match]] at the [[Money in the Bank (2019)|namesake]] pay-per-view on May 19.<ref name=\":28\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/126077/titles-vacated-entrants-named-for-both-mitb-matchesupdated-wwe-money-in-the-bank-ppv-lineup.html?p=1|title=TITLES VACATED, ENTRANTS NAMED FOR BOTH MITB MATCHES.....UPDATED WWE MONEY IN THE BANK PPV LINEUP|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=April 30, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":29\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/126087/wwe-smackdown-report-the-men-and-women-are-announced-for-mitb-bayley-versus-becky-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: THE MEN AND WOMEN ARE ANNOUNCED FOR MITB, BAYLEY VERSUS BECKY, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=April 30, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":30\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=126249&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: TITLE MATCHES, WILD CARD FEVER, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=May 7, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Deville, who was ringside during the match, tried to climb the ladder and help Rose win the match, however, [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]] was able to fight them off and retrieve the briefcase.<ref name=\":31\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=126559&p=2|title=COMPLETE WWE MONEY IN THE BANK REPORT: TWO LADDER MATCHES, TWO WOMEN'S TITLE MATCHES FOR BECKY, WHO SITS ON THE THRONES WITH THE BRIEFCASES, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=May 19, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> On the September 3 episode of ''SmackDown'', Rose and Deville, now dubbed as Fire & Desire, defeated Alexa Bliss and Nikki Cross to earn a Women's Tag Team Championship shot at [[Clash of Champions (2019)|Clash of Champions]].<ref name=\":32\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/2019-09-03/article/fire-and-desire-def-alexa-bliss-nikki-cross|title=Fire & Desire def. Alexa Bliss & Nikki Cross|website=WWE|accessdate=December 17, 2019}}</ref> At the event, the two failed to capture the title.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/wwe/story/_/id/27578808/wwe-clash-champions-news-stories-match-card-results-start-information|title=WWE Clash of Champions news, stories, match card, results, start time and information|date=September 9, 2019|website=ESPN.com}}</ref>\n\n==== Romance storyline (2019\u2013present) ====\nIn December 2019, Rose entered into a romantic [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#angle|storyline]] with [[Otis Dozovic|Otis]], with Otis helping Rose during her matches.<ref name=\"SmackDown12202019\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/12/20/12-20-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-big-e-and-kofi-kingston-vs-shinsuke-nakamura-and-cesaro-in-a-non-title-match-bayley-vs-dana-brooke-in-a-non-title-match/|title=12/20 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell's review Big E and Kofi Kingston vs. Shinsuke Nakamura and Cesaro in a non-title match, Bayley vs. Dana Brooke in a non-title match|date=December 20, 2019|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.f4wonline.com/wwe-news/otis-mandy-rose-date-set-valentines-day-wwe-smackdown-303181|title=Otis & Mandy Rose date set for Valentine's Day WWE SmackDown|website=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]|date=January 31, 2020|last=Rose|first=Bryan|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref> She later agreed to a date with him on Valentine's Day, but [[Dolph Ziggler]] appeared in Otis's place during the date, which resulted in a romance between Rose and Ziggler.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fightful.com/wrestling/truth-heard-sonya-deville-behind-mandy-rose-and-dolph-ziggler-relationship|website=Fightful|title=The Truth Is Heard: Sonya Deville Behind Mandy Rose And Dolph Ziggler Relationship|last=Lamber|first=Jeremy|date=April 3, 2020|access-date=April 6, 2020}}</ref> The storyline then evolved into a love triangle involving a feud between Ziggler and Otis over Rose.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fightful.com/wrestling/dolph-ziggler-challenges-otis-passion-driven-bout-wrestlemania-36|website=Fightful|date=March 27, 2020|title=Dolph Ziggler Challenges Otis To Passion-Driven Bout At WrestleMania 36|last=DeFelice|first=Robert|access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref> It was revealed on the April 3, 2020 episode of ''SmackDown'' that Deville was working with Ziggler to keep Otis from Rose.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prowrestlingsheet.com/hacker-glitches-smackdown-speaks-video/|website=Pro Wrestling Sheet|date=April 3, 2020|title=Hacker Behind Glitches On SmackDown Speaks, Reveals Sonya/Dolph Ziggler Plot|last=Satin|first=Ryan|access-date=April 6, 2020}}</ref> On April 5 at [[WrestleMania 36]], Rose interfered during a match between Otis and Ziggler by attacking Deville, who was at ringside, and Ziggler, which helped Otis score the victory. Following the match, she and Otis shared a kiss.<ref>{{cite web|website=[[USA Today]]|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/2020/04/05/wrestlemania-36-night-2-recap-match-breakdowns/2952351001/|title=Everything that happened on Night 2 of WrestleMania 36|date=April 5, 2020|last=Schwartz|first=Nick|access-date=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Other media ==\nRose has been featured in multiple fitness publications including ''[[Fitness Gurls]]'', ''Fit & Firm'', and ''FitFemme''.<ref name=\"signingofficial\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/97487/wwe-officially-announces-a-number-of-signings-including-tough-enough-competitors-evolve-alumni.html?p=1|title=WWE OFFICIALLY ANNOUNCES A NUMBER OF SIGNINGS INCLUDING TOUGH ENOUGH COMPETITORS & EVOLVE ALUMNI|author=Johnson, Mike|website=PWInsider|date=October 28, 2015|accessdate=October 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\nRose appeared as part of the main cast for the [[Total Divas (season 5)|fifth season]] of the WWE [[reality television]] series ''[[Total Divas]]'', which began airing in January 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/96472/wwe-signings-update.html?p=1|title=WWE SIGNINGS UPDATE|website=PWInsider|author=Johnson, Mike|date=September 9, 2015|accessdate=October 12, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"mandy\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/97051/name-of-wwes-newest-diva-revealed-total-divas-cast-changes-more-revealed.html?p=1|title=NAME OF WWE'S NEWEST DIVA REVEALED, TOTAL DIVAS CAST CHANGES & MORE REVEALED|author=Johnson, Mike|website=PWInsider|date=October 6, 2015|accessdate=October 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/totaldivas/article/total-bellas-coming-e-new-total-divas-cast-announced|title='Total Bellas' coming to E!, new 'Total Divas' cast announced|date=April 26, 2016|accessdate=August 5, 2016|publisher=[[WWE]]}}</ref>\n\nRose has appeared in two [[WWE]] [[video games]], debuting as a playable character in ''[[WWE 2K19]]'' and returning in ''[[WWE 2K20]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cole |first1=Caitlin |title=Complete WWE 2K19 Roster |url=https://rumbleramble.com/complete-wwe-2k19-roster/ |website=Rumble Ramble |accessdate=April 23, 2019 |date=December 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nSaccomanno participates in yoga, pilates, and [[CrossFit]].<ref name=\"wwebio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/superstars/mandy-rose|title=Mandy Rose|website=[[WWE]]|accessdate=February 27, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"USA Bio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.usanetwork.com/wwetoughenough/cast/amanda-saccomanno|title=CHARACTER BIO: AMANDA SACCOMANNO|accessdate=September 17, 2015|work=usanetwork.com|date=June 15, 2015}}</ref> In April 2018, she revealed that she was dating fellow professional wrestler [[Sabatino Piscitelli]], better known by the ring name Tino Sabbatelli.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lilian is Live from Wrestlemania 34! |url=http://www.podcastonesales.com/episode/Lilian-is-Live-from-Wrestlemania-34 |publisher=PodcastOne |accessdate=June 30, 2018 |date=April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[WWE Tough Enough]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Herself\n| Contestant; runner-up (season 6)\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Total Divas]]''\n| Main cast (season 5): 10 episodes <!-- as of the April 19 episode, 2016 -->\n|}\n\n== Championships and accomplishments ==\n\n=== Fitness modeling ===\n* '''World Bodybuilding Fitness & Fashion'''\n** 2014 WBFF Boston \u2013 (first place)\n** 2014 WBFF Diva Bikini Pro World Championship \u2013 (first place)\n\n=== Professional wrestling ===\n* '''''[[Pro Wrestling Illustrated]]'''''\n**Ranked No. 67 of the top 100 female wrestlers in the [[Pro Wrestling Illustrated#PWI Female 100|''PWI'' Female 100]] in 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wrestlingtravel.org/2019/11/01/pwi-top-100-female-wrestlers-2019-full-list/|title=The PWI Top 100 Female Wrestlers in the World|last=Big Daddy Kal|date=November 1, 2018|website=wrestlingtravel.org|url-status=live|access-date=November 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* '''''[[Sports Illustrated]]'''''\n** Ranked No. 15 in the top 30 female wrestlers in 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/wrestling/2018/12/28/wwe-wrestling-women-top-10-wrestlers-award|title=Counting down the top 10 women's wrestlers of 2018|first1=Justin|last1=Barrasso|website=SI.com|date=December 28, 2018|accessdate=June 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Amanda Saccomanno}}\n* {{wwe superstars|mandy-rose}}\n* {{Professional wrestling profiles|cagematch=16878|wrestlingdata=30204|iwd=mandy-rose-11904|name=Mandy Rose}}\n\n{{WWE personnel}}\n{{Total Divas}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rose, Mandy}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:American female professional wrestlers]]\n[[Category:American professional wrestlers of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:American female models]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:Fitness and figure competitors]]\n[[Category:Iona College (New York) alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Yorktown, New York]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestlers from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Tough Enough contestants]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American professional wrestler}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox professional wrestler\n|name         = Mandy Rose\n|image        = File:Mandy Rose.jpeg\n|caption      = Rose in April 2016\n|birth_name   = Amanda Rose Saccomanno\n|birth_date   = {{Birth date|mf=yes|1990|7|18}} or 1991 (age {{age|1991|7|18}}\u2013{{age|1990|7|18}})\n|birth_place  = [[Westchester County, New York]], U.S.\n|resides      =\n|height       = 5 ft 4 in<ref name=\"wwetoughenough2\"/><ref name=\"wwebio\"/>\n|names        = '''Mandy Rose'''<ref name=\"wwebio\"/>\n|weight       = 120 lb<ref name=\"wwetoughenough2\"/>\n|billed       = [[Yorktown Heights, New York]]<ref name=\"wwebio\"/>\n|trainer      = [[Booker T (wrestler)|Booker T]]<ref name=\"coaches\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwetoughenough.com/about|title=MEET THE COMPETITORS AND CAST OF WWE TOUGH ENOUGH|website=WWE Tough Enough|accessdate=October 6, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906221455/https://www.wwetoughenough.com/about|archive-date=September 6, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><br />[[Billy Gunn]]<ref name=\"coaches\"/><br />[[Lita (wrestler)|Lita]]<ref name=\"coaches\"/><br />[[WWE Performance Center]]<ref name=\"pc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwenxt/tough-enough-finalists-join-new-recruits-performance-center|title=Tough Enough competitors join new class of recruits at the WWE Performance Center|publisher=[[WWE]]|date=September 29, 2015|accessdate=August 5, 2016}}</ref>\n|debut        = August 25, 2015<ref name=\"IWD profile\">{{cite web|url=http://www.profightdb.com/wrestlers/amanda-saccomanno-11904.html|title=Amanda Saccomanno|website=Internet Wrestling Database (IWD)|accessdate=October 6, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Amanda Rose Saccomanno''' (born July 18, 1990<ref name=\"1990 Birthday\">Those giving 1990 include:\n*{{cite web |title=Mandy Rose on Instagram: \"Cheers to 29 years & many many more!! \ud83e\udd42\ud83c\udf7e\ud83c\udf89\ud83c\udf81\ud83d\ude4f\ud83c\udffb\ud83d\udc78#BestIsYetToCome #29nevaLookedSoGood \ud83e\udd11\" |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B0E8VyNH3BQ/ |website=Instagram |accessdate=August 7, 2019 |language=en}}\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/wrestling/2019/09/25/wwe-news-mandy-rose-shayna-baszler-flip-gordon|title=The Week in Wrestling: Mandy Rose Takes Unconventional Path to WWE Stardom|date=September 25, 2019|last=Barrasso|first=Justin|website=Sports Illustrated}}</ref> or 1991)<ref name=\"1991 Birthday\">Those giving 1991 include:\n*{{cite news |title=WWE Profile - Mandy Rose |url=https://www.espn.in/wwe/story/_/id/21654744/wwe-profile-page-mandy-rose |accessdate=July 19, 2019 |work=[[ESPN]] |date=December 3, 2017 |language=en}}\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/mandy-rose-wwe-smackdown-live-gods-greatest-creation/|title=WWE's Mandy Rose Is Building a Brand, and Being 'God's Greatest Creation' Is Just the Start|last=Maglio|first=Tony|date=July 23, 2019|website=The Wrap}}</ref> is an American [[Professional wrestling|professional wrestler]], television personality, and former fitness and figure competitor. She is signed to [[WWE]], where she performs under the [[ring name]] '''Mandy Rose''' on the company's [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] brand.\n\nRose began a professional fitness competition career in 2013 and went on to become a bodybuilding competitor the following year. In 2015, she placed second on the WWE competition ''[[WWE Tough Enough|Tough Enough]]'', after which she signed a contract with WWE and joined the [[reality television]] show ''[[Total Divas]]'' as a main cast member for one season. After a brief stint in WWE's developmental territory [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]], Rose made her main roster debut in 2017. She then competed alongside [[Sonya Deville]] as a tag team, dubbed Fire and Desire.\n\n== Early life ==\nAmanda Rose Saccomanno was born in the [[New York City]] suburb of [[Westchester County, New York]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/wwe-superstar-mandy-rose-wrestling-journey|website=Fox News|title=WWE Superstar Mandy Rose reflects on her journey to wrestling: 'It's kind of crazy'|date=January 11, 2020|last=Day|first=Nate}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.profightdb.com/wrestlers/amanda-saccomanno-11904.html|title=Amanda Saccomanno|website=The Internet Wrestling Database|accessdate=October 2, 2015}}</ref> The youngest of four children,<ref name=\"Interview\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwenxt/article/mandy-rose-interview|title=Meet Mandy Rose, NXT's \"Golden Goddess\"|date=October 14, 2016|accessdate=October 18, 2016|last=Byron|first=Saxton|authorlink=Byron Saxton|publisher=[[WWE]]}}</ref> she has Irish and Italian ancestry.<ref name=\"Interview\"/> Her childhood nickname was \"Hamburgers\".<ref name=\"USA Bio\"/> She attended [[Yorktown High School (New York)|Yorktown High School]], where she participated in dance. She later earned her [[bachelor's degree]] at [[Iona College (New York)|Iona College]], majoring in [[Speech-language pathology|speech pathology]].<ref name=\"Interview\"/><ref name=\"signingofficial\"/> She entered her first [[Fitness and figure competition|fitness competition]] in 2013, and took first place in the World Bodybuilding Fitness & Fashion Boston Show. She was also crowned the 2014 World Beauty Fitness & Fashion Bikini Champion.<ref name=\"signingofficial\"/>\n\n== Professional wrestling career ==\n=== WWE ===\n==== ''Tough Enough'' and NXT (2015\u20132017) ====\nSaccomanno was a contestant in the [[WWE Tough Enough#Season 6|sixth season]] of the [[WWE]] competition ''[[WWE Tough Enough]]'', which began airing in June 2015.<ref name=\"wwetoughenough2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwetoughenough.com/competitors/Amanda|title=Amanda Saccomanno &#124; Tough Enough|work=[[WWE Tough Enough]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829133205/https://www.wwetoughenough.com/competitors/Amanda |archive-date=August 29, 2018 |accessdate=May 22, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"wwetoughenough\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwetoughenough.com/news/meet-wwe-tough-enoughs-13-finalists|title=Meet WWE Tough Enough&#039;s 13 finalists &#124; Tough Enough|work=[[WWE Tough Enough]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140835/https://www.wwetoughenough.com/news/meet-wwe-tough-enoughs-13-finalists |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |accessdate=May 22, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"prweb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2015/06/prweb12801229.htm|title=Yorktown Heights' Amanda Saccomanno Advances to Final Round of Acclaimed WWE Competition|publisher=prweb.com|accessdate=July 6, 2015}}</ref> She was at risk of elimination on the July 28 episode, but was saved by judge [[The Miz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwetoughenough.com/video/mizs-save-costs-mada-wwe-tough-enough-july-28-2015|title=THE MIZ'S SAVE COSTS MADA: WWE TOUGH ENOUGH, JULY 28, 2015|website=WWE Tough Enough|date=July 28, 2015|accessdate=October 6, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151007110145/https://www.wwetoughenough.com/video/mizs-save-costs-mada-wwe-tough-enough-july-28-2015|archive-date=October 7, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> During the season finale, she adopted the [[ring name]] Mandy Rose, lost a match against [[Alicia Fox]], and placed second overall, after winners [[Sara Lee (wrestler)|Sara Lee]] and [[Josh Bredl]].<ref name=\"Tough Enough 25/08/15\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/96142/tough-enough-finale-report-who-are-the-two-newest-wwe-superstars.html?p=1#!|title=TOUGH ENOUGH FINALE REPORT: WHO ARE THE TWO NEWEST WWE SUPERSTARS?|last=Richard|first=Trionfo|date=August 25, 2015|accessdate=August 5, 2016|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\"final\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwetoughenough.com/news/wwe-tough-enough-recap-august-25-2015-and-winners-are|title=WWE Tough Enough recap, August 25, 2015: And the winners are...|work=[[WWE Tough Enough]]|date=August 25, 2015|accessdate=August 25, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150921171045/https://www.wwetoughenough.com/news/wwe-tough-enough-recap-august-25-2015-and-winners-are|archive-date=September 21, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAfter the ''Tough Enough'' season finale, it was revealed that Rose had signed a five-year contract with the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/97487/wwe-officially-announces-a-number-of-signings-including-tough-enough-competitors-evolve-alumni.html?p=1|title=WWE OFFICIALLY ANNOUNCES A NUMBER OF SIGNINGS INCLUDING TOUGH ENOUGH COMPETITORS & EVOLVE ALUMNI - PWInsider.com|website=www.pwinsider.com|accessdate=February 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/videos/total-divas-meet-mandy-rose-total-divas-preview-clip-february-2-2016|title=The 'Total Divas' meet Mandy Rose: Total Divas Preview Clip, February 2, 2016|accessdate=April 16, 2016|publisher=[[WWE]]}}</ref> Rose made her in-ring debut for WWE's [[Farm team#Professional wrestling|developmental territory]], [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]], during a [[Six-man tag team match|six-woman tag team match]] at a [[live event]] in [[Venice, Florida]] on January 30, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/99405/130-nxt-results-from-venice-fl.html?p=1|title=1/30 NXT RESULTS FROM VENICE, FL|author=Kiger, John|website=PWInsider|date=January 30, 2016|accessdate=January 31, 2016}}</ref> On the August 17 episode of ''NXT'', Rose debuted in a [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple man teamed matches|six-woman tag team match]] along with [[Daria Berenato]] and [[Alexa Bliss]], in which they were defeated by [[Carmella (wrestler)|Carmella]], [[Liv Morgan]], and [[Nikki Cross|Nikki Glencross]].<ref name=\"NXT 17/08/16\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/104125/wwe-nxt-report-what-could-go-wrong-with-opponents-in-the-same-room-itami-in-action-six-woman-tag-match-with-some-debuts-a-look-at-takeover-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE NXT REPORT: WHAT COULD GO WRONG WITH OPPONENTS IN THE SAME ROOM?, ITAMI IN ACTION, SIX WOMAN TAG MATCH WITH SOME DEBUTS, A LOOK AT TAKEOVER, AND MORE|last=Richard|first=Trionfo|work=PWInsider|date=August 17, 2016|accessdate=August 18, 2016}}</ref> On the September 28 episode of ''NXT'', Rose lost her first televised singles match to [[Ember Moon]].<ref name=\"NXT 28/09/16\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/105008/wwe-nxt-report-asuka-faces-liv-morgan-the-dusty-classic-starts-next-week-itami-versus-dorado-ember-moon-versus-mandy-rose-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE NXT REPORT: ASUKA FACES LIV MORGAN, THE DUSTY CLASSIC STARTS NEXT WEEK, ITAMI VERSUS DORADO, EMBER MOON VERSUS MANDY ROSE, AND MORE|last=Richard|first=Trionfo|date=September 28, 2016|accessdate=September 30, 2016|work=PWInsider}}</ref>\n\n==== Absolution and Fire and Desire (2017\u20132020) ====\n[[File:Mandy Rose&Sonya Deville WM34.jpg|thumb|upright|Rose (left) with [[Sonya Deville]] at [[WrestleMania 34]] in April 2018]]\nOn the November 20, 2017, episode of ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]'', Rose joined [[Sonya Deville]] and [[Paige (wrestler)|Paige]] as they attacked [[Sasha Banks]], [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]], [[Mickie James]], and [[Alexa Bliss]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=113734&p=2|title=WWE RAW REPORT: INTERCONTINENTAL TITLE MATCH, NEW FACES IN THE WOMEN'S DIVISION, THAT YOUNGSTER KANE CONTINUES HIS PATH OF TERROR, JOE VERSUS BALOR, AND MORE|last=Richard|first=Trionfo|date=November 20, 2017|work=PWInsider}}</ref> A week later, the trio's name was revealed as Absolution.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=113843&p=2|title=WWE RAW REPORT: THEY HAVE A NAME, WAS THIS ELIAS' NIGHT?, DANA FOUND A WEAKNESS, FATAL FOUR WAY MATCH, AND MORE|last=Richard|first=Trionfo|date=November 27, 2017|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Rose had her first televised match on the main roster at ''[[WWE Tribute to the Troops results#2017|Tribute to the Troops]]'' on December 19, where Absolution defeated Bayley, James, and Banks.<ref name=\"auto\"/> On January 28, 2018 at the [[Royal Rumble (2018)|Royal Rumble]], Rose entered the first [[Royal Rumble#Females|women's Royal Rumble match]] at number 4, and she was the first woman eliminated from the match by [[Lita (wrestler)|Lita]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=115167&p=4|title=FULL ROYAL RUMBLE COVERAGE|last=Strode|first=Cory|date=January 28, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> In February, Rose took part of the inaugural women's [[Elimination Chamber|Elimination Chamber match]], which was won by Bliss.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=115732&p=2|title=COMPLETE WWE ELIMINATION CHAMBER PPV COVERAGE INCLUDING RAW TALK COVERAGE|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=February 25, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> In April, Paige retired from the ring due to neck injuries and became the [[SmackDown (brand)|SmackDown]] general manager.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=116741&p=2|title=WWE RAW REPORT: NEW TALENT FROM NXT, A FORMER CHAMPION RETURNS, THE STATUS OF THE TAG TEAM TITLES, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=April 9, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> In her first [[WrestleMania]] appearance, at [[WrestleMania 34]], Rose participated in the [[WrestleMania Women's Battle Royal]], which would be won by [[Naomi (wrestler)|Naomi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=116716&p=2|title=COMPLETE WRESTLEMANIA 34 KICKOFF SHOW COVERAGE|last=Carapola|first=Stuart|date=April 8, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref>\n\nBoth Rose and Deville were drafted to SmackDown during the [[2018 Superstar Shake-up]], with Paige subsequently declaring that Absolution was over.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=116903&p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: NEW FACES, STYLES AND BRYAN AS A TAG TEAM, CHAMPIONS CHANGE BRANDS, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=April 17, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=117209&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: SOMEONE NEEDS TO APOLOGIZE, JOE SETS HIS SIGHTS ON GOLD, TAG MATCH, TRIOS WOMEN'S ACTION, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=May 1, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Despite this, Rose would continue competing in various tag team matches alongside Deville.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=117794&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: WHO IS THE LAST IN MITB?, ASUKA IN ACTION, A DANCE OFF, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=May 29, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=118077&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: A SUMMIT THAT TURNS INTO A MATCH, HARDY VERSUS NAKAMURA, AJ TALKS TO LAWLER, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=June 12, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://pwinsider.com/article/119635/wwe-smackdown-report-pen-pals-with-samoa-joe-a-trilogy-of-vignettes-about-miz-and-bryan-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: PEN PALS WITH SAMOA JOE, A TRILOGY OF VIGNETTES ABOUT MIZ AND BRYAN, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=August 14, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/120230/wwe-smackdown-report-tell-us-a-story-mr-samoa-joe-we-have-opponents-for-the-new-day-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: TELL US A STORY MR. SAMOA JOE, WE HAVE OPPONENTS FOR THE NEW DAY, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=September 11, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":7\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=121220&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: WORLD CUP PARTICIPANTS IN ACTION, FOOTAGE FROM THE PERFORMANCE CENTER, MIZTV, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=October 23, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Seeds of dissolution between the two were planted when Rose eliminated Deville from a [[Battle royal (professional wrestling)|battle royal]] at the inaugural all women's pay-per-view, [[WWE Evolution]].<ref name=\":8\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=121345&p=1|title=NIKKI BELLA VS. RONDA ROUSEY, LAST WOMAN STANDING, NXT WOMEN'S TITLE & MORE WWE EVOLUTION PPV COVERAGE|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=October 28, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> At [[Survivor Series (2018)|Survivor Series]] in November, Rose competed in her first traditional [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Elimination tag team matches|five-on-five elimination match]] as part of Team SmackDown in a losing effort.<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|url=https://pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=121586&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: TEAMS FOR SURVIVOR SERIES ANNOUNCED, BECKY IN ACTION, A DEBUT, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=November 6, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":10\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/121867/nakamura-vs-rollins-live-ongoing-wwe-survivor-series-2018-ppv-coverage.html?p=1|title=BROCK LESNAR VS. DANIEL BRYAN, CHARLOTTE FLAIR VS. RONDA ROUSEY, RAW VS. SMACKDOWN & MORE: COMPLETE WWE SURVIVOR SERIES 2018 PPV COVERAGE|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=November 18, 2018|accessdate=November 18, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref> After Survivor Series, the dissolution between Rose and Deville dissipated as the two continued their alliance, while Rose began a feud with Naomi due to Rose purposefully flirting with Naomi's husband.<ref name=\":11\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=122078&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: THE WOMEN'S TITLE MATCH IS SET, A NEW MASK COLLECTOR, USOS VERSUS BAR, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=November 27, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":13\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/122356/match-set-for-205-live-bray-resurrected-naomi-vs-mandy-and-more-wwe-news-notes.html?p=1|title=MATCH SET FOR 205 LIVE, BRAY RESURRECTED?, NAOMI VS. MANDY AND MORE WWE NEWS & NOTES|last=Jordan|first=Paul|date=December 8, 2018|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":14\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/122867/wwe-smackdown-report-who-is-daniel-bryans-opponent-in-phoenix-the-man-makes-a-statement-a-new-fashion-files-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: WHO IS DANIEL BRYAN'S OPPONENT IN PHOENIX?, THE MAN MAKES A STATEMENT, A NEW FASHION FILES, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=January 1, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":16\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/123259/wwe-smackdown-report-almas-versus-mysterio-joe-takes-out-some-anger-happy-birthday-the-man-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: ALMAS VERSUS MYSTERIO, JOE TAKES OUT SOME ANGER, HAPPY BIRTHDAY, THE MAN, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=January 15, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":17\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/123461/wwe-smackdown-report-almas-and-mysterio-two-out-of-three-falls-bryan-and-styles-tony-chimmel-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: ALMAS AND MYSTERIO TWO OUT OF THREE FALLS, BRYAN AND STYLES, TONY CHIMMEL, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=January 22, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> The rivalry continued as both Rose and Naomi eliminated each other from the women's [[Royal Rumble match]] at the [[Royal Rumble (2019)|Royal Rumble]] event, on January 27, 2019, where Rose managed to last 25:50.<ref name=\":18\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=123626&p=5|title=COMPLETE WWE ROYAL RUMBLE 2019 COVERAGE|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=January 27, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> The feud ended in February after the two exchanged victories over each other.<ref name=\":19\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=123893&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: A TASTE OF WHAT IS TO COME AT THE ELIMINATION CHAMBER?, CAN RUSEV AND NAKAMURA WORK TOGETHER, AND THE MAN PLAYS THE GAME|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=February 5, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":20\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/124095/wwe-smackdown-report-who-is-the-last-in-the-wwe-championship-match-who-is-first-in-the-womens-tag-match-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: WHO IS THE LAST IN THE WWE CHAMPIONSHIP MATCH?, WHO IS FIRST IN THE WOMEN'S TAG MATCH, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=February 12, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref>\n\nOn February 17, at the [[Elimination Chamber (2019)|Elimination Chamber]] pay-per-view, Rose and Deville competed in a six-team [[Elimination Chamber match]] for the inaugural [[WWE Women's Tag Team Championship]], where they started the match against and were then the final team eliminated by [[Sasha Banks]] and [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]], who won the match in the process.<ref name=\":21\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=124221&p=2|title=SMACKDOWN TAG TITLE MATCH: LIVE ONGOING WWE ELIMINATION CHAMBER PPV COVERAGE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=February 17, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Rose then competed in the second WrestleMania Women's Battle Royal during the [[WrestleMania 35]] pre-show in a losing effort.<ref name=\":26\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/wrestlemania-35/wrestlemania-womens-battle-royal|title=WrestleMania Women's Battle Royal Match|work=WWE|accessdate=March 29, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":27\">{{cite web|url=https://pwinsider.com/article/125534/live-ongoing-wrestlemania-35-preshow-coverage-womens-battle-royal.html?p=1|title=COMPLETE WRESTLEMANIA 35 KICKOFF SHOW COVERAGE|last=Carapola|first=Stuart|date=April 7, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Rose then competed in the [[Money in the Bank ladder match]] at the [[Money in the Bank (2019)|namesake]] pay-per-view on May 19.<ref name=\":28\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/126077/titles-vacated-entrants-named-for-both-mitb-matchesupdated-wwe-money-in-the-bank-ppv-lineup.html?p=1|title=TITLES VACATED, ENTRANTS NAMED FOR BOTH MITB MATCHES.....UPDATED WWE MONEY IN THE BANK PPV LINEUP|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=April 30, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":29\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/126087/wwe-smackdown-report-the-men-and-women-are-announced-for-mitb-bayley-versus-becky-and-more.html?p=1|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: THE MEN AND WOMEN ARE ANNOUNCED FOR MITB, BAYLEY VERSUS BECKY, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=April 30, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref><ref name=\":30\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=126249&p=2|title=WWE SMACKDOWN REPORT: TITLE MATCHES, WILD CARD FEVER, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=May 7, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> Deville, who was ringside during the match, tried to climb the ladder and help Rose win the match, however, [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]] was able to fight them off and retrieve the briefcase.<ref name=\":31\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=126559&p=2|title=COMPLETE WWE MONEY IN THE BANK REPORT: TWO LADDER MATCHES, TWO WOMEN'S TITLE MATCHES FOR BECKY, WHO SITS ON THE THRONES WITH THE BRIEFCASES, AND MORE|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|date=May 19, 2019|work=PWInsider}}</ref> On the September 3 episode of ''SmackDown'', Rose and Deville, now dubbed as Fire & Desire, defeated Alexa Bliss and Nikki Cross to earn a Women's Tag Team Championship shot at [[Clash of Champions (2019)|Clash of Champions]].<ref name=\":32\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/2019-09-03/article/fire-and-desire-def-alexa-bliss-nikki-cross|title=Fire & Desire def. Alexa Bliss & Nikki Cross|website=WWE|accessdate=December 17, 2019}}</ref> At the event, the two failed to capture the title.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/wwe/story/_/id/27578808/wwe-clash-champions-news-stories-match-card-results-start-information|title=WWE Clash of Champions news, stories, match card, results, start time and information|date=September 9, 2019|website=ESPN.com}}</ref>\n\n==== Romance storyline (2019\u2013present) ====\nIn December 2019, Rose entered into a romantic [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#angle|storyline]] with [[Otis Dozovic|Otis]], with Otis helping Rose during her matches.<ref name=\"SmackDown12202019\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/12/20/12-20-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-big-e-and-kofi-kingston-vs-shinsuke-nakamura-and-cesaro-in-a-non-title-match-bayley-vs-dana-brooke-in-a-non-title-match/|title=12/20 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell's review Big E and Kofi Kingston vs. Shinsuke Nakamura and Cesaro in a non-title match, Bayley vs. Dana Brooke in a non-title match|date=December 20, 2019|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.f4wonline.com/wwe-news/otis-mandy-rose-date-set-valentines-day-wwe-smackdown-303181|title=Otis & Mandy Rose date set for Valentine's Day WWE SmackDown|website=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]|date=January 31, 2020|last=Rose|first=Bryan|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref> She later agreed to a date with him on Valentine's Day, but [[Dolph Ziggler]] appeared in Otis's place during the date, which resulted in a romance between Rose and Ziggler.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fightful.com/wrestling/truth-heard-sonya-deville-behind-mandy-rose-and-dolph-ziggler-relationship|website=Fightful|title=The Truth Is Heard: Sonya Deville Behind Mandy Rose And Dolph Ziggler Relationship|last=Lamber|first=Jeremy|date=April 3, 2020|access-date=April 6, 2020}}</ref> The storyline then evolved into a love triangle involving a feud between Ziggler and Otis over Rose.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fightful.com/wrestling/dolph-ziggler-challenges-otis-passion-driven-bout-wrestlemania-36|website=Fightful|date=March 27, 2020|title=Dolph Ziggler Challenges Otis To Passion-Driven Bout At WrestleMania 36|last=DeFelice|first=Robert|access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref> It was revealed on the April 3, 2020 episode of ''SmackDown'' that Deville was working with Ziggler to keep Otis from Rose.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prowrestlingsheet.com/hacker-glitches-smackdown-speaks-video/|website=Pro Wrestling Sheet|date=April 3, 2020|title=Hacker Behind Glitches On SmackDown Speaks, Reveals Sonya/Dolph Ziggler Plot|last=Satin|first=Ryan|access-date=April 6, 2020}}</ref> On April 5 at [[WrestleMania 36]], Rose interfered during a match between Otis and Ziggler by attacking Deville, who was at ringside, and Ziggler, which helped Otis score the victory. Following the match, she and Otis shared a kiss.<ref>{{cite web|website=[[USA Today]]|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/2020/04/05/wrestlemania-36-night-2-recap-match-breakdowns/2952351001/|title=Everything that happened on Night 2 of WrestleMania 36|date=April 5, 2020|last=Schwartz|first=Nick|access-date=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Other media ==\nRose has been featured in multiple fitness publications including ''[[Fitness Gurls]]'', ''Fit & Firm'', and ''FitFemme''.<ref name=\"signingofficial\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/97487/wwe-officially-announces-a-number-of-signings-including-tough-enough-competitors-evolve-alumni.html?p=1|title=WWE OFFICIALLY ANNOUNCES A NUMBER OF SIGNINGS INCLUDING TOUGH ENOUGH COMPETITORS & EVOLVE ALUMNI|author=Johnson, Mike|website=PWInsider|date=October 28, 2015|accessdate=October 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\nRose appeared as part of the main cast for the [[Total Divas (season 5)|fifth season]] of the WWE [[reality television]] series ''[[Total Divas]]'', which began airing in January 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/96472/wwe-signings-update.html?p=1|title=WWE SIGNINGS UPDATE|website=PWInsider|author=Johnson, Mike|date=September 9, 2015|accessdate=October 12, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"mandy\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/97051/name-of-wwes-newest-diva-revealed-total-divas-cast-changes-more-revealed.html?p=1|title=NAME OF WWE'S NEWEST DIVA REVEALED, TOTAL DIVAS CAST CHANGES & MORE REVEALED|author=Johnson, Mike|website=PWInsider|date=October 6, 2015|accessdate=October 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/totaldivas/article/total-bellas-coming-e-new-total-divas-cast-announced|title='Total Bellas' coming to E!, new 'Total Divas' cast announced|date=April 26, 2016|accessdate=August 5, 2016|publisher=[[WWE]]}}</ref>\n\nRose has appeared in two [[WWE]] [[video games]], debuting as a playable character in ''[[WWE 2K19]]'' and returning in ''[[WWE 2K20]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cole |first1=Caitlin |title=Complete WWE 2K19 Roster |url=https://rumbleramble.com/complete-wwe-2k19-roster/ |website=Rumble Ramble |accessdate=April 23, 2019 |date=December 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nSaccomanno participates in yoga, pilates, and [[CrossFit]].<ref name=\"wwebio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/superstars/mandy-rose|title=Mandy Rose|website=[[WWE]]|accessdate=February 27, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"USA Bio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.usanetwork.com/wwetoughenough/cast/amanda-saccomanno|title=CHARACTER BIO: AMANDA SACCOMANNO|accessdate=September 17, 2015|work=usanetwork.com|date=June 15, 2015}}</ref> In April 2018, she revealed that she was dating fellow professional wrestler [[Sabatino Piscitelli]], better known by the ring name Tino Sabbatelli.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lilian is Live from Wrestlemania 34! |url=http://www.podcastonesales.com/episode/Lilian-is-Live-from-Wrestlemania-34 |publisher=PodcastOne |accessdate=June 30, 2018 |date=April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[WWE Tough Enough]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Herself\n| Contestant; runner-up (season 6)\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Total Divas]]''\n| Main cast (season 5): 10 episodes <!-- as of the April 19 episode, 2016 -->\n|}\n\n== Championships and accomplishments ==\n\n=== Fitness modeling ===\n* '''World Bodybuilding Fitness & Fashion'''\n** 2014 WBFF Boston \u2013 (first place)\n** 2014 WBFF Diva Bikini Pro World Championship \u2013 (first place)\n\n=== Professional wrestling ===\n* '''''[[Pro Wrestling Illustrated]]'''''\n**Ranked No. 67 of the top 100 female wrestlers in the [[Pro Wrestling Illustrated#PWI Female 100|