        = $97\u2013127 million<ref name=BOM>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=wolverine2017.htm |title=Logan (2017) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=July 14, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414135302/https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl3229320705/ |archive-date=April 14, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Faughnder |first=Ryan |url=http://www.latimes.com/business/hollywood/la-fi-ct-movie-projector-logan-20170227-story.html |title=Hugh Zaid Mak's last movie, 'Logan,' is going to shred its box-office competition |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=March 1, 2017 |accessdate=February 23, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414135356/https://www.latimes.com/business/hollywood/la-fi-ct-movie-projector-logan-20170227-story.html |archive-date=April 14, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| gross          = $619 million<ref name=BOM/>\n}}\n'''''Logan''''' is a 2017 American [[superhero film]] starring [[Hugh Jackman]] as [[Wolverine (character)|the titular character]]. It is the tenth film in the [[X-Men (film series)|''X-Men'' film series]] and the third and final installment in the ''Wolverine'' trilogy following ''[[X-Men Origins: Wolverine]]'' (2009) and ''[[The Wolverine (film)|The Wolverine]]'' (2013). The film, which takes inspiration from <!-- Do NOT add \"loose\" or an other potentially contentious labels per WP:W2W, See talk page for more info --> \"[[Old Man Logan#Original story|Old Man Logan]]\" by [[Mark Millar]] and [[Steve McNiven]], based in an alternate bleak future, follows an aged Wolverine and an extremely ill Charles Xavier who defend a young mutant named [[X-23|Laura]] from the villainous [[Reavers (comics)|Reavers]] led by [[Donald Pierce]] and [[Zander Rice]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/08/11/hugh-jackman-photo-old-man-logan-speculation|title=Hugh Jackman photos spark 'Old Man Logan' speculation|last=Coggan|first=Devan|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=August 11, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414135736/https://ew.com/article/2016/08/11/hugh-jackman-photo-old-man-logan-speculation/|archive-date=April 14, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/10/20/old-man-logan-comparison-from-comics-to-movie|title=OLD MAN LOGAN COMPARISON: FROM COMICS TO MOVIE|last=Collura|first=Scott|website=[[IGN]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414135845/https://www.ign.com/articles/2016/10/20/old-man-logan-comparison-from-comics-to-movie|archive-date=April 14, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.flickeringmyth.com/2016/10/behold-old-man-logan-in-new-image-from-the-wolverine-sequel/|title=Behold Old Man Logan in new image from the Wolverine sequel|last=Cranswick|first=Amie|publisher=FlickeringMyth.com|date=October 19, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414140032/https://www.flickeringmyth.com/2016/10/behold-old-man-logan-in-new-image-from-the-wolverine-sequel/|archive-date=April 14, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The film is produced by [[20th Century Fox]], [[Marvel Entertainment]], [[TSG Entertainment]] and The Donners' Company, and distributed by 20th Century Fox.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.econotimes.com/Wolverine-3-Updates-Production-Moves-from-Louisiana-to-New-Mexico-Hugh-Jackman-Hits-Gym-for-Intense-Training-for-Role-Shows-Off-New-Video-of-Work-Out-243228|title=Wolverine 3 Updates: Production Moves from Louisiana to New Mexico; Hugh Jackman Hits Gym for Intense Training for Role, Shows Off New Video of Work Out |first=|work=[[The Economic Times]]|date=August 2, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ProducedByFox\">{{cite web | url = https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-boxoffice/box-office-logan-roars-with-massive-85-3-million-debut-idUSKBN16C0SL | title = Box Office: 'Logan' roars with massive $85.3 million debut | publisher = [[Reuters]] | first = Brent | last = Lang | date = March 5, 2017 | accessdate = January 13, 2020}}</ref> It is directed by [[James Mangold]], who co-wrote the screenplay with Michael Green and Scott Frank, from a story by Mangold.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/10/logan-trailer-hugh-jackman-wolverine-film-1201839705/|title='Logan': First Trailer For Hugh Jackman's Latest Wolverine Turn|last=Petski|first=Denise|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref> In addition to Jackman, the film also stars [[Patrick Stewart]], [[Richard E. Grant]], [[Boyd Holbrook]], [[Stephen Merchant]], and [[Dafne Keen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/logan-wolverine-3-trailer-hugh-jackman-x-23-a7371771.html|title=Logan trailer: First clip for Wolverine 3 features Hugh Jackman's Old Man Logan and Patrick Stewart's Professor X|last=Shepherd|first=Jack|work=[[The Independent]]|location=UK|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.starburstmagazine.com/movie-news/16642-dafne-keen-is-logans-x-23|title=Dafne Keen is LOGAN's X-23|last=Pollard|first=Andrew|work=[[Starburst (magazine)|Starburst]]|date=October 25, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.flickeringmyth.com/2016/11/hugh-jackmans-wolverine-featured-in-new-logan-image-and-storyboards/|title=Elise Neal Joins WOLVERINE 3|last=Collinson|first=Gary|publisher=FlickeringMyth.com|date=November 1, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n[[Principal photography]] began in [[Louisiana]] on May 2, 2016, and wrapped on August 19, 2016, in [[New Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/filming-dates-locations-avatar-2-wolverine-3-transformers-5-other-big-upcoming-films-revealed-1541395|title=Filming dates and locations for Avatar 2, Wolverine 3, Transformers 5 and other big upcoming films revealed?|last=Varma|first=Arjun|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=February 2, 2016|accessdate=November 11, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-3-avatar-2-filming-start-dates/|title='Wolverine 3', 'Avatar 2' Rumored to Start Shooting in April|last=Trumbore|first=Dave|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=February 1, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/x-men/news/a805304/hugh-jackman-wraps-up-filming-his-final-wolverine-movie/|title=Watch: Hugh Jackman Celebrates the End of 'Wolverine 3' Filming with a Nice Shave|last=Anderton|first=Joe|website=[[Digital Spy]]|date=August 20, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> The locations used for ''Logan'' were mainly in Louisiana, New Mexico, and [[Mississippi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.flickeringmyth.com/2016/06/first-wolverine-3-set-photos-show-hugh-jackmans-logan-sporting-a-beard/|title=First Wolverine 3 set photos show Hugh Jackman's Logan sporting a beard|last=Cook|first=Justin|publisher=FlickeringMyth.com|date=June 1, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/marvel/2016/08/19/wolverine-3-wraps-filming/|title=Wolverine 3 Wraps Filming|last=Mueller|first=Matthew|work=ComicBook.com|date=August 19, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.auditionsfree.com/2016/new-casting-calls-marvels-wolverine-3-la/|title=New Casting Calls on Marvel's \"Wolverine 3\" in LA|publisher=AuditionsFree.com|date=June 27, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref> Jackman makes his final appearance as Wolverine in the film, having portrayed the character in eight of the nine previous films in the ''X-Men'' series. Stewart also makes his final appearance as Professor X, having portrayed the character in six films in the series.\n\n''Logan'' premiered at the [[67th Berlin International Film Festival]] on February 17, 2017, and was theatrically released in the United States on March 3, 2017, in [[IMAX]] and standard formats. The film received critical acclaim, with much praise for its screenplay, direction, acting (particularly that of Jackman, Stewart, and Keen), action sequences, emotional depth, and departure from traditional superhero films.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.seattletimes.com/entertainment/movies/what-critics-are-saying-about-logan/ |title=What the Critics are saying about Logan |newspaper=[[Seattle Times]] |date=March 3, 2017 |accessdate=January 24, 2018}}</ref> It became one of the best-reviewed films in the ''X-Men'' franchise, with many critics regarding it as one of the [[List of films considered the best#Superhero|greatest superhero films ever made]],<ref name=greatest/> and it was selected by the [[National Board of Review]] as one of the [[National Board of Review Awards 2017#Top 10 Films|top ten films of 2017]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalboardofreview.org/2017/11/national-board-review-announces-2017-award-winners/ |title=National Board of Review Announces 2017 Award Winners |publisher=[[National Board of Review]] |date=November 28, 2017 |accessdate=December 7, 2017}}</ref> It was nominated for [[Academy Award for Best Adapted Screenplay|Best Adapted Screenplay]] at the [[90th Academy Awards]], becoming the first live-action superhero film ever to be nominated for screenwriting.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/list-2018-oscar-nominations-1202668757/|title=Oscar Nominations 2018: The Complete List|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=January 23, 2018 |accessdate=January 23, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"First Adapted Hero\">{{cite web |url=http://ew.com/movies/2018/01/23/logan-oscar-nomination-comics/ |title=Logan is the first Oscar-nominated screenplay based on superhero comics |last=Holub |first=Christian |date=January 23, 2018 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=Time Inc. |access-date=January 25, 2018}}</ref> It grossed over $619 million worldwide and became the <!-- DO NOT CHANGE THE RANKING. AS HAS BEEN SAID ***MULTIPLE TIMES*** PEAK POSITION IS TO BE MAINTAINED IN THESE ARTICLES. -->[[List of highest-grossing R-rated films|fourth-highest-grossing R-rated film]]<!-- DO NOT CHANGE THE RANKING. AS HAS BEEN SAID ***MULTIPLE TIMES*** PEAK POSITION IS TO BE MAINTAINED IN THESE ARTICLES. --> of all time.\n\n==Plot==\nIn 2029, no [[Mutant (Marvel Comics)|mutants]] have been born in 25 years. An aging [[Wolverine (character)|Logan]]'s healing ability is failing. Working as a limo driver in [[El Paso, Texas]], he and mutant tracker [[Caliban (Marvel Comics)|Caliban]] care for 90-year-old [[Professor X|Charles Xavier]], Logan's mentor and founder of the [[X-Men]], in an abandoned [[Smelting|smelting plant]] in northern Mexico. Xavier has developed [[dementia]] that causes him to have destructive seizures; it is alluded that one year prior, one such seizure released a powerful wave of his telepathic powers that resulted in the deaths of six hundred people, including several of the X-Men.\n\nLogan reluctantly agrees to escort Gabriela Lopez, a former nurse for biotechnology corporation Alkali-Transigen, and a young girl, [[X-23|Laura]], to Eden, a refuge in [[North Dakota]]. Later finding Gabriela dead, Logan is confronted at his Mexican hideout by her killer [[Donald Pierce]], who is Transigen's [[cyborg]] chief of security. Pierce is looking for Laura, who has stowed away in Logan's limo and has similar powers to him. She, Logan, and Xavier escape Pierce and his [[Reavers (comics)|Reavers]], but Caliban is tortured into tracking Laura.\n\nA video on Gabriela's cellphone shows that Transigen created Laura and other children from mutant DNA to become weapons; Laura was created from Logan's DNA. As they proved difficult to control and Transigen found an alternative, the children were to be killed, but Gabriela and other nurses helped some escape. In [[Oklahoma City]], Logan discovers that Eden appears in Laura's X-Men comic and tells her it is fictional. The Reavers arrive, but Xavier has a seizure and incapacitates everyone except Logan and Laura, who kill the attackers and inject Xavier with his medication. As they flee, [[List of Marvel Comics characters: R#Zander Rice|Dr. Zander Rice]], head of Transigen, arrives to help Pierce.\n\nLogan, Laura, and Xavier help farmer Will Munson and his family after a traffic incident, accepting an offer of dinner at their home, where Logan drives off enforcers from a corporate farm. Rice unleashes X-24, a clone of Logan in his prime and his alternative to the child program, who murders Will's family and Xavier, stabbing Will and capturing Laura. Caliban sets off grenades, killing himself and several Reavers while injuring Pierce. Logan is outmatched by X-24, but Will pins X-24 with his truck before dying from his injuries. Logan and Laura escape with Xavier's body.\n\nAfter burying Xavier, Logan passes out. Laura takes him to a doctor and persuades him to prove that the site in North Dakota is not Eden. There, they find [[Rictor]] and other Transigen children preparing to cross into Canada. Laura finds an adamantium bullet that Logan has kept since his escape from the [[Weapon X]] facility, which he once considered using to commit suicide. Logan decides that his job is done and chooses not to accompany them, to Laura's dismay.\n\nWhen the Reavers capture the children, Logan takes an overdose of a serum given to him by Rictor that temporarily enhances his healing abilities and boosts his strength. With Laura's help, he slaughters most of the Reavers before the serum wears off. As Pierce holds Rictor at gunpoint, Rice tells Logan, who killed Rice's father years ago at the Weapon X facility, that no new mutants have been born due to genetically engineered crops created by Transigen and distributed through the world's food supply. Logan, having found a gun, shoots Rice and injures Pierce. X-24, enraged by Rice's death, fights Logan, as the children combine their powers to kill Pierce and the remaining Reavers. Rictor uses his powers to flip a truck onto X-24, but he frees himself and impales Logan on a large tree branch. Laura uses Logan's revolver and adamantium bullet to shoot X-24 in the head.\n\nNear death, Logan tells Laura not to become the weapon that she was made to be, and after she tearfully acknowledges him as her father, he dies peacefully in her arms. Laura and the children bury Logan, and Laura turns his grave marker on its side to create an X, honoring him as a member of the X-Men before she and the children depart for the Canadian border.\n\n==Cast==\n[[File:World Premiere Logan Berlinale 2017.jpg|thumb|upright|Portraying the character for 17 years in nine films earned Jackman the [[Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record]] of the \"longest career as a live-action Marvel superhero\".]]\n* [[Hugh Jackman]] as [[Wolverine (character)|Logan / Wolverine]]:\n:The X-Man formerly-known as the Wolverine and a physically [[adamantium|enhanced]] mutant with accelerated healing, dealing with his age and ailment as well as Charles Xavier's former pupil, and Laura's biological father.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2016/10/19/13332326/wolverine-logan-hugh-jackman|title=Wolverine looks old and tired in this first look from Logan|last=Alexander|first=Julia|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|date=October 19, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref name=Empire>{{cite web|url=http://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/logan-trailer-breakdown-james-mangold-talks-us-first-teaser/|title='Logan': Wolverine 3 Key Roles Revealed (Exclusive)|last=O'Hara|first=Helen|work=[[Empire (magazine)|Empire]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> He is one of Charles Xavier's caregivers, alongside Caliban.<ref name=Details/> Mangold spoke of Logan's age influencing his regenerative capabilities, which he stated may no longer produce soft skin, \"so we imagined he heals quickly, still, but it leaves a scar. The simple idea was that his body would start to get a little more ravaged with a kind of tattooing of past battles, lacerations that remain of previous conflicts.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/wolverine/news/a811807/wolverine-still-has-healing-powers-in-logan/|title=Don't worry, Wolverine still has healing powers in Logan|last=Davies|first=Megan|website=[[Digital Spy]]|date=October 21, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/logan-wolverine-scars-james-mangold/|title=Logan Director Explains Wolverine's Scars In The Film|last=Agar|first=Chris|publisher=ScreenRant.com|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> On the second page of the screenplay, Mangold spoke of Logan as \"... he's older now and it's clear his abilities aren't what they once were. He's fading on the inside and his diminished healing factor keeps him in a constant state of [[chronic pain]]\u2014hence booze as a painkiller.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbr.com/report-logan-film-to-introduce-x-23/|title=REPORT: LOGAN FILM TO INTRODUCE X-23|last=White|first=Brett|website=[[Comic Book Resources]]|date=October 6, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/news/1563329/official-wolverine-3-script-page-reveals-some-fascinating-details|title=Official Wolverine 3 Script Page Reveals Some Fascinating Details|last=Shepherd|first=Jack|publisher=CinemaBlend.com|date=October 5, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> In 2015, Jackman requested fan input for the direction Wolverine's story should go in the next film, while seeming to confirm that the project would serve as his farewell to Logan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/33688933/hugh-jackman-asks-for-ideas-from-fans-for-his-final-outing-as-wolverine|title=Hugh Jackman asks for ideas from fans for his final outing as Wolverine |publisher=[[BBC]]|date=July 28, 2015|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> To prepare for his role, Jackman ate a minimum of six meals per day, when working with trainer Mike Ryan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coachmag.co.uk/exercises/celebrity-workouts/146/exclusive-hugh-jackman-wolverine-workout|title=Hugh Jackman Workout: How He Got Ripped for Wolverine|last=Snape|first=Joel|work=Coach|date=March 31, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> Ryan stated that an average workout session for Jackman lasts up to three hours, beginning at 4:00 a.m.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.foods4betterhealth.com/wolverine-3-logan-actor-hugh-jackman-looks-fit-for-role-20415|title=Wolverine 3: Logan Actor Hugh Jackman Looks Fit for Role|last=Yaneff|first=Jon|publisher=Foods4BetterHealth.com|date=October 10, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> Jackman stated, \"... it's going to be very different. Very different in tone and hopefully different to anything we've done.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/10/04/hugh-jackman-teases-wolverine-3-different-tone|title=Hugh Jackman teases Wolverine 3 as 'very different in tone'|last=Coggan|first=Devan|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=October 4, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> Regarding the more personal tone Jackman noted \"That's always been really his dilemma, coming to terms with who he is\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.empireonline.com/people/hugh-jackman/hugh-jackman-reveals-empire-exclusive-logan-cover/|title=Hugh Jackman Reveals Empire's Exclusive Logan Cover|last=Nugent|first=John|work=Empire|date=January 24, 2017|accessdate=January 2, 2018}}</ref> Jackman has also explained that comedian [[Jerry Seinfeld]] was indirectly responsible for his decision to stop playing Logan after 17 years, with Jackman stating, \"I was having a chat with [Seinfeld] about a year ago ... he was talking about why he finished ''[[Seinfeld]]'' ... He said he'd always had this feeling and belief that you never know when either your energy or the audience's energy is going to dip over into people [saying] 'Oh, please go.'\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/hugh-jackman-explains-why-jerry-801353|title=Hugh Jackman Explains Why Jerry Seinfeld Is Behind the End of Wolverine|last=McMillan|first=Graeme|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=June 9, 2015|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref> Jackman accepted a pay reduction to ensure that the film would be produced to receive an [[Motion Picture Association of America film rating system|R-rating]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/hugh-jackman-took-a-paycut-to-make-sure-logan-was-rated-r-a7470901.html |title=Logan: Hugh Jackman took a pay cut to make sure his final Wolverine film would be rated R |last=Carissimo |first=Justin |date=December 12, 2016 |website=[[The Independent]] |accessdate=December 14, 2016}}</ref>\n:* Jackman also plays X-24, a feral younger clone of Wolverine, loyal only to his creator Zander Rice.\n* [[Patrick Stewart]] as [[Professor X|Charles Xavier / Professor X]]:\n:A mutant who is the world's most powerful [[Telepathy|telepath]] who is also founder and former leader of the now-defunct [[X-Men]]. He was formerly known as Professor X.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbcamerica.com/anglophenia/2016/10/first-look-professor-x-appears-spent-in-logan|title=First Look: Professor X Appears Spent in 'Logan'|last=Brown|first=Brigid|publisher=[[BBC America]]|date=October 6, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/190729-whos-the-girl-in-the-logan-trailer-x-23-could-be-making-her-debut-video|title=Who's The Girl In The 'Logan' Trailer? X-23 Could Be Making Her Debut \u2014 VIDEO|last=Lulic|first=Michelle|work=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Charles's telepathic abilities have become unstable due to age (over 90 years) and an unknown brain disease, and at times he does not even recognize Logan.<ref name=Details/> During the events of ''Logan'', Xavier is cared for by Logan and Caliban.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/marvel/2016/10/10/wolverine-3-logan-key-roles-possibly-revealed/|title=Wolverine 3: Logan Key Roles Possibly Revealed|last=Peters|first=Megan|publisher=Comicbook.com|date=October 10, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Regarding Xavier and the themes of aging and loneliness, Mangold said,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.joblo.com/movie-news/james-mangold-breaks-down-the-first-fantastic-trailer-for-logan-137?id=james-mangold-breaks-down-the-first-fantastic-trailer-for-logan-137&order=desc|title=JAMES MANGOLD BREAKS DOWN THAT FANTASTIC FIRST TRAILER FOR LOGAN|last=Fraser|first=Kevin|publisher=[[JoBlo.com]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> \"We've seen these characters in action, saving the universe. But what happens when you're in retirement and that career is over? ...<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.darkhorizons.com/mangold-talks-logan-timeline-and-tone/|title=Mangold Talks \"Logan\" Timeline And Tone|last=Franklin|first=Garth|work=[[Dark Horizons]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> The really interesting thing to me, or a place to dig that hadn't been dug, was the idea of mutants when they're no longer useful to the world, or even sure if they can do what they used to do. Their powers are diminished like all of ours are by age ...<ref name=Empire/> Our Charles is a very sweet character in this film. I think he's always been an incredibly sweet character. With the addition of his own physical fragility in this movie, he becomes an incredibly powerful paternal figure in the movie. Logan is more of a reluctant one, I think you can easily guess.\"<ref name=Digital>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/wolverine/feature/a819368/logan-director-james-mangold-breaks-down-violent-new-trailer-wolverine-x-men-movie/|title=Exclusive: Logan director James Mangold gives us a scene-by-scene breakdown of his explosive new trailer|last=Fletcher|first=Rosie|website=Digital Spy|date=January 19, 2017|accessdate=January 20, 2017}}</ref> Stewart remarked that \"... this is probably the end of this franchise for me. But the thing about science fiction and fantasy is that you can never, ever say it's the end, it's over.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.itv.com/news/calendar/update/2016-08-09/new-wolverine-film-probably-the-end-of-the-franchise-for-sir-patrick-stewart/ |title=New Wolverine film 'probably the end of the franchise' for Sir Patrick Stewart |publisher=[[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] |date=August 9, 2016 |accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Richard E. Grant]] as [[List of Marvel Comics characters: R#Zander Rice|Dr. Zander Rice]]:\n:The surgical head of ''Transigen'',<ref name=\"Transigen\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/logan-wolverine-3-key-roles-revealed-exclusive/|title='Logan': Wolverine 3 Key Roles Revealed (Exclusive)|last=Gonzalez|first=Umberto|publisher=TheWrap.com|date=October 10, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> whose father was killed by Logan during his escape from [[Weapon X]] Headquarters at Alkali Lake.<ref>''Logan'' - \"''You will recognise Dr. Zander Rice as the son of a man Wolverine murdered during his escape from the [[Weapon X]] programme.''\" - ''Empire'': March 2017 Issue - Page 62</ref> On the character of Rice, Mangold stated, \"He's the puppet master behind Pierce and the Reavers, and has a much larger role in the sense that he's actually the kind of brilliant mind that is trying to grow mutants.\"<ref name=\"Digital\" />\n* [[Boyd Holbrook]] as [[Donald Pierce]]:\n:''Transigen''{{'}}s relentless, calculating and intense head of security, and leader of the militant [[Reavers (comics)|Reavers]]<ref name=Digital/><ref name=Transigen/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/x-men/feature/a795439/wolverine-x-men-who-are-the-reavers/|title=Logan and the X-Men: who are the Reavers and what do they want with Wolverine?|last=Armitage|first=Hugh|website=Digital Spy|date=October 19, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/logan-reavers-confirmed-wolverine-3-939244|title='Logan' Photo Confirms Appearance of Classic X-Men Villains|last=Couch|first=Aaron|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=October 18, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> who is sent to retrieve Laura, which brings him into conflict with Wolverine. Holbrook said of the character, \"He's an innovative engineer and he's a big fan of Wolverine. He just wants to hang out with him ... There's a lot of surprising stuff in it.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/features/news/a17644/boyd-holbrook-narcos-interview/|title=#MANCRUSHMONDAY: BOYD HOLBROOK ON TAKING DOWN PABLO ESCOBAR|last=Kosin|first=Julie|work=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|date=September 12, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Mangold praised Holbrook's performance, saying that \"[he] is just a fabulous actor. I wanted this film to feel intimate and real and truthfully acted, and I wanted very much to break away from the kind of bloated feeling I've gotten from a lot of comic-book movies.\"<ref name=Digital/>\n* [[Stephen Merchant]] as [[Caliban (Marvel Comics)|Caliban]]:\n:An [[albinism in biology|albino]] mutant who can sense and track other mutants, who is helping Logan take care of Xavier.<ref name=Details>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/logan-wolverine-3-plot-details-revealed-exclusive/|title=Inside 'Logan': Wolverine 3 Plot Details Revealed (Exclusive)|last=Gonzalez|first=Umberto|publisher=[[TheWrap.com]]|date=October 10, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> On Merchant taking the role, Mangold mentioned, \"I'm always interested to find the thing that looks most interesting on the actors. Stephen is a huge man. One of the things that is so wonderful filming with him for a character like this is that he's a good six inches taller than Logan, and huge over Patrick. The little kid in the movie would come up to basically his knee. So there's a wonderful sense of scale\u2014but he has heart too.\" Mangold concluded by stating, \"... So that was a wonderful energy to enter the movie, and someone who instead of turning things into their own energy kind of joined ours.\"<ref name=Empire/> A younger Caliban was previously portrayed by [[T\u00f3mas Lemarquis]] in ''[[X-Men: Apocalypse]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/who-is-caliban-history-stephen-938974|title=What Caliban's Return in 'Logan' Means for the 'X-Men' Universe|last=McMillan|first=Graeme|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=October 17, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Dafne Keen]] as [[X-23|Laura]]:\n:A mysterious young girl, who is \"very much\" like Logan. She is also subject \"X-23\".<ref name=Empire/><ref name=Transigen/> On Keen's portrayal of Laura, Mangold mentioned, \"If anyone could steal a movie from [Jackman], it would be Dafne. She carries, all the time, a slight strangeness.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://heroichollywood.com/logan-director-james-mangold-making-human-wolverine-film-praises-dafne-keen/|title='Logan' Director James Mangold On Making A \"Human\" Wolverine Film; Praises Dafne Keen|last=Peris|first=Sebastian|publisher=HeroicHollywood.com|date=November 25, 2016|accessdate=November 26, 2016}}</ref> In an interview with ''Digital Spy'', Mangold stated, \"... [Keen] was 11 years old when we were shooting. She's a remarkable kid. Her parents are actors, and she's kind of a very modern kid. Very physically capable. Incredibly gifted as an actress. I mean, it was a huge risk for Fox to allow me to make a movie where the third point of the triangle was built upon someone so young.\" Mangold stated that the worldwide search for an actress to portray Laura was one in which he was seeking \"someone who was bilingual because I wanted a [[Latino (demonym)|Latina]] kid\u2014one who was between 10 and 12, and was a credible child.\" He later stated of Laura that: \"She's an 11-year-old girl equipped with all the volatility, instability, mood swings, shadows and potential violence of our hero.\"<ref name=Digital/> Co-writer [[Scott Frank]] pushed for the character to speak as little as possible when he joined the project to avoid making her into a typical kid sidekick, explaining, \"I read a few other drafts of the script that Jim worked on, and in all those drafts she was talking from the beginning and had an attitude. I thought that was a giant mistake.\"<ref name=\"McKittrick\">{{cite web|url=https://creativescreenwriting.com/logan/|title=Myth vs. Man: James Mangold and Scott Frank on Logan|last=McKittrick|first=Christopher|work=Creative Screenwriting|date=March 3, 2017|accessdate=March 10, 2017}}</ref> Sienna Novikov served as Keen's stunt double.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://omegaunderground.com/2016/10/10/young-actress-possibly-playing-x-23-logan-revealed-gymnast-sienna-novikov/|title=Update: Young Actress Possibly Playing X-23 In 'Logan' Revealed To Be Gymnast/Fencer Sienna Novikov?|last=Marc|first=Christopher|publisher=OmegaUnderground.com|date=October 10, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020085739/http://omegaunderground.com/2016/10/10/young-actress-possibly-playing-x-23-logan-revealed-gymnast-sienna-novikov/|archive-date=October 20, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://omegaunderground.com/2016/10/19/dafne-keen-confirmed-leaked-trailer-playing-x-23-logan/|title=Confirmed: Dafne Keen Is Playing The Girl (Laura aka X-23) In 'Logan'|last=Marc|first=Christopher|work=OmegaUnderground/com|date=October 19, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026043353/http://omegaunderground.com/2016/10/19/dafne-keen-confirmed-leaked-trailer-playing-x-23-logan/|archive-date=October 26, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAdditionally, [[Eriq La Salle]], [[Elise Neal]] and [[Elizabeth Rodriguez]] appear as Will Munson, Kathryn Munson, and Gabriela Lopez.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/article/ers-eriq-la-salle-glower-hugh-jackman-wolverine-3-236335|title=ER's Eriq La Salle to glower at Hugh Jackman in Wolverine 3|last=Hughes|first=William|work=[[The A.V. Club]]|date=May 5, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.starburstmagazine.com/movie-news/15064-elise-neal-joins-wolverine-3|title=Elise Neal Joins WOLVERINE 3|last=Pollard|first=Andrew|work=[[Starburst (magazine)|Starburst]]|date=May 6, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"EW\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/05/18/wolverine-3-elizabeth-rodriguez|title=Wolverine 3 adding Fear The Walking Dead alum Elizabeth Rodriguez to cast|last=Robinson|first=Will|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=May 18, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref> Doris Morgado, David Kallaway, Han Soto, [[Jason Genao]], [[Krzysztof Soszynski]], and [[Alison Fernandez]] appear as Maria, Danny Rhodes, Valet, [[Rictor]], Mohawk, and Delilah, respectively.<ref name=\"EW\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/10/logan-trailer-hugh-jackman-wolverine-film-1201839705/|title='Logan': First Trailer For Hugh Jackman's Latest Wolverine Turn|last=Petski|first=Denise|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/news/1567469/logan-just-confirmed-more-villains-for-wolverine-with-a-lethal-new-picture|title=Logan Just Confirmed More Villains for Wolverine With A Lethal New Picture|date=October 18, 2016|publisher=CinemaBlend.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lafilacero.com/actores/han-soto/|title=Han Soto - Actor|publisher=LaFilaCero}}</ref> In the commentary to ''X-Men: Apocalypse'', director [[Bryan Singer]] had stated that his film's [[post-credits scene]] would directly connect with the on-screen debut of ''X-Men'' antagonist [[Mister Sinister]] in ''Logan''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-3-mister-sinister-bryan-singer/|title=Mister Sinister Confirmed as Villain in 'Wolverine 3' by Bryan Singer|last=Cabin|first=Chris|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=September 12, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/09/12/x-men-director-singer-reportedly-reveals-mr-sinister-in-wolverine-3|title=X-MEN DIRECTOR SINGER REPORTEDLY REVEALS MR. SINISTER IN WOLVERINE 3|last=Porter|first=Matt|website=IGN|date=September 12, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/wolverine-3-villain-mister-sinister-hugh-jackman-old-man-logan/|title='Wolverine 3' Will Feature Villain Mister Sinister|last=Otterson|first=Joe|publisher=TheWrap.com|date=September 13, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/article/wolverine-3-will-introduce-mister-sinister-242456|title=Wolverine 3 will introduce Mister Sinister|last=Chavez|first=Danette|work=The A.V. Club|date=September 11, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2016/09/12/mister-sinister-in-the-third-wolverine-movie-can-save-x-men-from-magneto-overload/|title=Mister Sinister In Third 'Wolverine' Can Save 'X-Men' From Magneto Overload|last=Mendelson|first=Scott|work=[[Forbes]]|date=September 12, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref> In January 2017, Mangold stated that the character would not appear in this film. However, the DNA from several mutants, including Logan, in that film was used to create the clones that are seen in this film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/wolverine-3-logan-villains-mr-sinister/|title=Why Mister Sinister Really Doesn't Belong In Logan, According To The Director|publisher=Cinema Blend|last=O'Connell|first=Sean|date=January 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\n{{quote box\n| align = right\n| width = 35%\n| quote = [[Hugh Jackman|Hugh]] and I have been talking about what we would do since we were working on the last one, and for both of us it was this requirement that, to be even interested in doing it, we had to free ourselves from some assumptions that had existed in the past, and be able to change the tone a bit. Not merely to change for change's sake, but also to make something that's speaking to the culture now, that's not just the same style\u2014how many times can they save the world in one way or another? How can we construct a story that's built more on character and character issues, in a way as if it almost wasn't a superhero movie, yet it features their powers and struggles and themes?\n| source =\u2014[[James Mangold]], on the development and approach of ''Logan''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/logan-timeline-explained-james-mangold/#images|title='Logan': James Mangold Reveals Timeline; Teases Film's Unique Tone and Family Focus|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n\nIn November 2013, [[20th Century Fox]] initiated discussions over another solo film starring Wolverine, with [[James Mangold]] in negotiations to write the treatment for the film and [[Lauren Shuler Donner]] returning to produce under The Donners' Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2013/11/james-mangold-hugh-jackman-sinking-claws-into-another-the-wolverine-film-627461/|title=James Mangold, Hugh Jackman Sinking Claws Into Another 'The Wolverine' Film|last=Fleming Jr|first=Mike|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=November 5, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2013/12/06/storylines-we-want-to-see-in-wolverine-3|title=STORYLINES WE WANT TO SEE IN WOLVERINE 3|last=Schedeen|first=Jesse|website=IGN|date=December 6, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2013/film/news/wolverine-james-mangold-x-men-1200797970/|title=Hugh Jackman, James Mangold Lining Up for Another 'Wolverine' Film|last=Variety Staff|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=November 5, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wolverine-sequel-works-james-mangold-653337|title='Wolverine' Sequel in the Works With James Mangold|last=McClintock|first=Pamela|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=November 5, 2013|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> At the time, [[Hugh Jackman]] neither confirmed nor denied his reprisal of Logan in a new film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scifinow.co.uk/news/the-wolverine-2-hugh-jackman-reveals-cool-ideas-for-script/|title=The Wolverine 2: Hugh Jackman Reveals 'Cool Ideas' for Script|last=Glick|first=Martin|work=[[SciFiNow]]|date=November 15, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/hugh-jackman-talks-third-wolverine-solo-movie/|title=Hugh Jackman Talks Up Third Wolverine Solo Movie|last=Plumb|first=Ali|work=Empire|date=November 15, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> Jackman clarified that his lapsing contract with Fox, which reportedly would need to be renegotiated after ''[[X-Men: Days of Future Past]]'' (2014),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2013/11/13/hugh-jackman-wolverine-sequel|title=Hugh Jackman on 'The Wolverine' sequel, Neill Blomkamp's 'Chappie,' musicals he's eyeing|last=Beard|first=Lanford|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=November 13, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> did not mean he was leaving the franchise, as he had been working movie-by-movie since ''[[X2 (film)|X2]]'' (2003).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://me.ign.com/en/movies/73719/news/jackman-on-wolverine-sequel-it-has-to-be-great|title=JACKMAN ON WOLVERINE SEQUEL: 'IT HAS TO BE GREAT'|last=O'Brien|first=Lucy|website=IGN|date=November 17, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> He also stated, \"I do want to do it with Jim and with [producer] Lauren Shuler-Donner because we had such a great experience. I'm really proud of ''[[The Wolverine (film)|The Wolverine]]'' (2013).\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/the-wolverine-3-sequel-news-hugh-jackman/|title=Hugh Jackman Talks THE WOLVERINE Sequel; Says 'There Are Some Really Cool Ideas'|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=November 14, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> Later in the month, Mangold announced that the [[pre-production]] aspect of the film had not yet begun, nor the writing process, though he furthered this by stating, \"... I would say I'm not there yet. But I have taken finger to key. Let's say that. There's been typing. And ideas. And talking amongst all the principles.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/the-wolverine-2-sequel-james-mangold-interview/|title=Director James Mangold Talks Developing THE WOLVERINE for Fox, Depicting Japan in the Film, and the Status of THE WOLVERINE 2|last=Cook|first=Tommy|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=November 19, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\nShortly after the release of ''The Wolverine'', Mangold spoke of a potential sequel with the aim of not converting it into a \"Will the world survive?\" film, while also stressing his need \"... not to make the same picture again.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/wolverine-3-classic-costume-james-mangold-explained/|title=James Mangold Talks Wolverine 3 & Classic Yellow Costume|last=Keyes|first=Rob|publisher=ScreenRant.com|date=November 21, 2013|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/the-wolverine-2-sequel-james-mangold-interview/|title=James Mangold Talks THE WOLVERINE, Making a Different Kind of Superhero Movie, His Action Style, the Editing Process, 3D, and More|last=Weintraub|first=Steve|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=June 25, 2013|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> In December 2013, Jackman spoke of nearing the end of his tenure as the character, while stating that the film was in the very early stages of development.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2013/12/hugh-jackman-wolverine-interview|title=Hugh Jackman on Why He Shoots Wolverine Dialogue Scenes in the Morning, and What a Nice Guy Rupert Murdoch Is|last=Miller|first=Julie|work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|date=December 5, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> Jackman also revealed that Mangold and he had begun speaking of potential ideas, adding, \"... Jim Mangold and I were literally on the phone last night talking about ideas but there is no script and no writer yet so it's a way off.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2013/12/06/hugh-jackman-says-he-may-not-do-the-next-wolverine-movie|title=HUGH JACKMAN SAYS HE MAY NOT DO THE NEXT WOLVERINE MOVIE|last=Cornet|first=Roth|website=IGN|date=December 6, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> Mangold would later reveal that Jackman was very involved in developing the story, saying, \"Hugh and I have been friends for almost twenty years now, and he was there every step of the way. For Hugh and I, the first goal was to construct something more intimate. Hugh often brought up ''[[The Wrestler (2008 film)|The Wrestler]]'' and ''[[Unforgiven]]'' as examples. I used those references as well as others. I pitched to both Hugh and the studio that I had an idea for an extremely bloody, existential ''[[Little Miss Sunshine]]''.\"<ref name=\"McKittrick\"/>\n\nBy March 2014, a decision was made to begin shooting after [[Bryan Singer]]'s ''[[X-Men: Apocalypse]]'' (2016), with the tentative plan to shoot the films [[Back to back film production|back-to-back]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/the-wolverine-2-filming-after-x-men-apocalypse/|title=James Mangold Says He's Planning to Shoot THE WOLVERINE 2 after Bryan Singer Films X-MEN: APOCALYPSE|last=Goldberg|first=Matt|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=March 16, 2014|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/the-wolverine-2-filming-after-x-men-apocalypse/|title=Hugh Jackman Talks Leaving the Character of Wolverine Behind; Considers Whether He'd Rather Be Rebooted or Replaced|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=March 13, 2014|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> with producer Hutch Parker stating, \"... the goal will be ''X-Men: Apocalypse'' for 2016, which means at the latest [filming begins] in summer 2015, and then the same thing with ''Wolverine'', either before or after, but based on the script.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/tag/wolverine-3/#page/8|title=Wolverine to Appear in X-MEN: APOCALYPSE; Will Likely Shoot Back-to-Back with Next WOLVERINE Movie|last=Goldberg|first=Matt|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=May 9, 2014|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Also in March, 20th Century Fox set a release date of March 3, 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2014/03/fox-unveils-dates-for-fantastic-four-wolverine-sequels-untitled-marvel-pic-702534/|title=Fox Unveils Dates For 'Fantastic Four' & 'Wolverine' Sequels, Untitled Marvel Pic|last=The Deadline Team|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 20, 2014|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/fantastic-four-2-release-date-wolverine-sequel-release-date/|title=Fox Announces Release Dates for THE FANTASTIC FOUR 2, WOLVERINE Sequel, Untitled Marvel Film, TAKEN 3, Ridley Scott Project, and More [Updated]|last=Bettinger|first=Brendan|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=March 20, 2014|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> Mangold boarded the project as director,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/fox-sets-dates-wolverine-fantastic-690143|title=Fox Sets Dates for 'Wolverine,' 'Fantastic Four' Sequels|last=Couch|first=Aaron|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=March 20, 2014|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> Jackman signed on to reprise his role,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-2-sequel-david-james-kelly/|title=Fox Sets Screenwriter David James Kelly for WOLVERINE Sequel; Director James Mangold and Star Hugh Jackman Expected to Return|last=Trumbore|first=Dave|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 22, 2014|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> and David James Kelly was hired to pen the screenplay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2014/03/fox-sets-david-james-kelly-to-script-next-wolverine-702889/|title=Fox Sets David James Kelly To Script Next 'Wolverine'|last=Fleming Jr|first=Mike|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 22, 2014|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> In April 2014, Jackman spoke about his ambitious feelings for the character of Logan, while mentioning that they can go further than what they achieved in ''The Wolverine''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/hugh-jackman-99-9-percent-sure-wolverine-sequel-will-last-x-men-movie/|title=Hugh Jackman '99.9 Percent' Sure 'Wolverine' Sequel Will Be His Last 'X-Men' Movie|last=Gilman|first=Greg|publisher=TheWrap.com|date=April 30, 2014|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Jackman also expressed his feelings of finality with portraying the character of Logan,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashionnstyle.com/articles/52245/20150317/wolverine-3-movie-cast-top-5-actors-who-can-replace-hugh-jackman-if-he-leaves-marvel-franchise.htm|title='Wolverine 3' Movie Cast: Top 5 Actors Who Can Replace Hugh Jackman If He Leaves Marvel Franchise|last=Cornejo|first=Jordianne|work=Fashion & Style|date=March 17, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113032726/http://www.fashionnstyle.com/articles/52245/20150317/wolverine-3-movie-cast-top-5-actors-who-can-replace-hugh-jackman-if-he-leaves-marvel-franchise.htm|archive-date=November 13, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> while in terms of storyline, he explained that nothing had been decided as of yet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themarysue.com/hugh-jackman-wolverine-tasm2-mary-jane-scene/|title=Comic Book Movie Roundup: (Almost) Au Revoir Hugh Jackman, TASM2 Director On the Mary Jane Scene That Almost Was|last=Pahle|first=Rebecca|publisher=[[Mary Sue|TheMarySue.com]]|date=May 1, 2014|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Jackman concluded by highlighting that the success of the script development would determine whether Jackman would return at all:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/the-wolverine-2-last-hugh-jackman/|title=Hugh Jackman Says the Next Solo WOLVERINE Movie Will Probably Be His Last Performance as the Character|last=Goldberg|first=Matt|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=April 30, 2014|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> \"I haven't signed on. I'm genuinely at that point where unless it's better than the last one I'm not going to do it. I think it has to be better. I can still see where we can improve on the last one. I love the intimacy of that story, I liked the small stuff, I liked that it was a little unexpected.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/hugh-jackman-teases-his-final-700201|title=Hugh Jackman Teases His Final Wolverine Appearance|last=McMillan|first=Graeme|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=April 30, 2014|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2015, [[Patrick Stewart]] spoke of discussions about the third Wolverine film, centering around a team-up between Jackman's Wolverine and himself as Charles Xavier,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/movies/2015/02/patrick_stewart_raves_about_po.html#incart_river|title=Patrick Stewart raves about Portland while discussing his new film 'Match'|last=Mohan|first=Marc|work=[[The Oregonian]]|date=February 7, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-movie-patrick-stewart-hugh-jackman/|title=Patrick Stewart Says He May Co-Star with Hugh Jackman in the Next WOLVERINE Movie|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=February 9, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> with Stewart stating to Marc Mohan that \"... we have been talking about a Wolverine movie, which would team Hugh Jackman and myself together ... That would be a very different sort of ''X-Men'' from the four movies that I've already done.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2015/02/10/patrick-stewart-says-hes-back-for-next-wolverine-movie-mckellenmagneto-joining-x-men-apocalypse|title=Patrick Stewart Says He's Back for Next Wolverine Movie, McKellen/Magneto Joining X-Men: Apocalypse|last= Couto|first=Anthony|publisher=[GN|date=February 9, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/x-men-patrick-stewart-hints-771939|title='X-Men': Patrick Stewart Hints at Old Xavier's Return in 2017|last=McMillan|first=Graeme|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 9, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> By April 2015, [[Michael Green (writer)|Michael Green]] had taken over screenwriting duties, with Mangold still actively overseeing the script development process.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/hugh-jackmans-wolverine-lands-blade-runner-2-writer-michael-green-exclusive/|title=Hugh Jackman's 'Wolverine' Lands 'Blade Runner 2' Writer Michael Green (Exclusive)|last=Geier|first=Thom|publisher=The Wrap.com|date=April 24, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> In September 2015, Jackman spoke of the writers being halfway through the script, and that the story would delve into the relationship between Wolverine and Professor X,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-3-hugh-jackman-on-patrick-stewart-professor-x-father-son-relationship/|title=Hugh Jackman Says 'Wolverine 3' Explores the Professor X Father/Son Relationship|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=September 24, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> to which he added, \"I think it's a really important relationship but I want to see signs of that quasi-father/son sort of relationship that has not been seen before, and sides of particularly Professor X that have not been seen before.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themarysue.com/wolverine-3-father-son-relationship/|title=Hugh Jackman Says Wolverine 3 Will Explore Father/Son Relationship With Professor X|last=Jao|first=Charline|publisher=TheMarySue.com|date=September 25, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/x-men/news/a670465/wolverine-3-to-focus-on-the-fatherson-like-relationship-with-professor-x/|title=Wolverine 3 to focus on the father/son-like relationship with Professor X|last=Hegarty|first=Tasha|website=Digital Spy|date=September 26, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Jackman spoke of Mangold's plan to start filming the next year, though he expressed uncertainty as to filming locations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slashfilm.com/hugh-jackman-updates-wolverine-3-development-progress/|title=Hugh Jackman Won't Shoot 'Wolverine 3' Until the Script Is Perfect|last=Anderton|first=Ethan|publisher=[[/Film]]|date=September 26, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Also in September, [[Mark Millar]], creative consultant for Fox, confirmed that Mangold's film would be a loose adaptation of the ''[[Old Man Logan]]'' story, something that was hinted at earlier by Jackman.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2015/09/25/mark-millar-explains-how-a-wolverine-old-man-logan-movie-could-work-without-marvel-studios-characters|title=MARK MILLAR EXPLAINS HOW A WOLVERINE: OLD MAN LOGAN MOVIE COULD WORK WITHOUT MARVEL STUDIOS CHARACTERS|last=Yehl|first=Joshua|website=IGN|date=September 25, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> In October 2016, the title of the film was announced as ''Logan''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/wolverine-3-hugh-jackman-title-xmen-1201878837/|title=Hugh Jackman Reveals Title of Upcoming Wolverine Film|last=Kelley|first=Seth|work=Variety|date=October 5, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/uk/news/799983/logan-is-back-hugh-jackman-reveals-final-wolverine-title-and-poster|title=Logan Is Back! Hugh Jackman Reveals Final Wolverine Title and Poster|last=Schnurr|first=Samantha|publisher=[[E!]]|date=October 5, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2016, Jackman confirmed that Mangold had a full screenplay, albeit not complete.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/hugh-jackman-wolverine-3-script-update/|title='Wolverine 3' Script Update from Hugh Jackman|last=Goldberg|first=Matt|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=January 26, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> The following month, [[Liev Schreiber]] expressed interest in returning to portray [[Sabretooth (comics)|Victor Creed / Sabretooth]], with Jackman himself mentioning Mangold's vision to Schreiber. After the film's release, it was revealed by Jackman that originally the script had the character play a role in the film, but that Sabretooth was excluded from the final screenplay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/news/1631149/what-logan-was-planning-to-do-with-sabretooth|title=What Logan Was Planning To Do With Sabretooth|date=March 2, 2017|publisher=CinemaBlend.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2747082/liev-schreiber-sabretooth-wolverine-3/|title=WILL LIEV SCHREIBER REPRISE 'OLD MAN SABRETOOTH' IN WOLVERINE 3?|last=Bell|first=Crystal|publisher=[[MTV]]|date=February 29, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-3-liev-schreiber-sabretooth/|title='Wolverine 3': Liev Schreiber Confirms Talks of Reprising Sabretooth|last=Romano|first=Nick|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=February 29, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2016/02/29/liev-schreiber-has-talked-to-hugh-jackman-about-returning-as-sabretooth-for-wolverine-3|title=LIEV SCHREIBER HAS TALKED TO HUGH JACKMAN ABOUT RETURNING AS SABRETOOTH FOR WOLVERINE 3|last=Passalacqua|first=Michael|website=IGN|date=February 29, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/news/a664228/is-liev-schreiber-coming-back-as-sabretooth-for-wolverine-3/|title=Is Liev Schreiber coming back as Sabretooth for Wolverine 3?|last=Armitage|first=Hugh|website=Digital Spy|date=August 29, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> By April 2016, Mangold had chosen [[Boyd Holbrook]] to portray the main antagonist of the movie,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/narcos-star-boyd-holbrook-talks-882221|title='Narcos' Star Boyd Holbrook in Talks for 'Wolverine 3' Villain|last=Galuppo|first=Mia|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=April 8, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/boyd-holbrook-in-negotiations-to-play-wolverine-3-villain/|title=Boyd Holbrook in Negotiations to Play 'Wolverine 3' Villain|last=Donnelly|first=Matt|publisher=TheWrap.com|date=April 8, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-3-boyd-holbrook-villain/|title='Wolverine 3' Recruits 'Narcos' Star Boyd Holbrook for Villainous Role|last=Foutch|first=Haleigh|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=April 8, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> the chief of security for a global corporation that is pursuing Wolverine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/boyd-holbrook-wolverine-3-hugh-jackman-1201749479/|title=Boyd Holbrook to Play Villain in 'Wolverine 3'|last=McNary|first=Dave|work=Variety| date=April 8, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/wolverine-3-boyd-holbrook-lead-villain-hugh-jackman-patrick-stewart-1201734367/|title='Wolverine 3' Sets 'Narcos' Boyd Holbrook As Chief Villain|last=Patten| first=Dominic|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 8, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Also by April, [[Richard E. Grant]] was cast as a villainous [[mad scientist]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wolverine-3-finds-mad-scientist-888038|title='Narcos' Star Boyd Holbrook in Talks for 'Wolverine 3' Villain|last=Kit|first=Borys|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=April 26, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-3-richard-e-grant/|title='Wolverine 3' Adds Richard E. Grant as a Mad Scientist-Esque Villain|last=Romano|first=Nick|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=April 27, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> and [[Stephen Merchant]] had also been cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/stephen-merchant-wolverine-3-hugh-jackman-x-men-1201745268/|title=Stephen Merchant To Star With Hugh Jackman In 'Wolverine 3'|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 27, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/stephen-merchant-wolverine-3-hugh-jackman-1201762380/|title=Stephen Merchant Joins Hugh Jackman's 'Wolverine 3'|last=McNary|first=Dave|work=Variety|date=April 27, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/wolverine-3-stephen-merchant-goes-bald-for-x-men-film-role-a7004831.html|title=Wolverine 3: Stephen Merchant goes bald for X-Men film role|last=Loughrey|first=Clarisse|work=The Independent|location=UK|date=April 28, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/apr/28/stephen-merchant-joining-wolverine-3-hugh-jackman-richard-e-grant|title=Stephen Merchant joins the cast of Wolverine 3|last=Lee|first=Benjamin|work=[[The Guardian]]|location=UK|date=April 28, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/article/stephen-merchant-play-some-intimidating-badass-wol-235952|title=Stephen Merchant to play some intimidating badass in Wolverine 3|last=Barsanti|first=Sam|work=The A.V. Club|date=April 27, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> In May, [[Eriq Lasalle]] and [[Elise Neal]] were cast supporting roles,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/eriq-lasalle-wolverine-3-1201766800/|title=Eriq Lasalle Joins Cast of 'Wolverine 3'|last=Kroll|first=Justin|work=Variety|date=May 4, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/elise-neal-wolverine-3-1201767705/|title=Elise Neal Joins 'Wolverine 3'|last=Kroll|first=Justin|work=Variety|date=May 5, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> and [[Elizabeth Rodriguez]] entered negotiations for a small but key role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/wolverine-3-poised-to-add-fear-the-walking-deads-elizabeth-rodriguez-exclusive/|title=Boyd Holbrook to Play Villain in 'Wolverine 3'|last=Geier|first=Thom|work=[[TheWrap]]|date=May 18, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.empireonline.com/people/hugh-jackman/elizabeth-rodriguez-joining-new-wolverine/|title=Elizabeth Rodriguez is joining the new Wolverine|last=White|first=James|work=[[Empire (magazine)|Empire]]|date=May 19, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Also in May, producer [[Simon Kinberg]] revealed that filming had already begun, and confirmed that the movie would be [[Motion Picture Association of America film rating system|R-rated]]; regarding the setting and tonality,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-3-villains/|title=Rumor: 'Wolverine 3' Villains May Have Just Been Revealed|last=Romano|first=Nick|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=May 25, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> he stated, \"It takes place in the future, and as you and others have reported, it is an R-rated movie. It's violent, it's kind of like a western in its tone. It's just a very cool, different film.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hugh-jackmans-wolverine-targets-r-868897|title=Hugh Jackman's Final 'Wolverine' Movie Targets R Rating|last=White|first=James|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=February 24, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-3-filming-rated-r/|title=Wolverine 3 Has Started Filming; Simon Kinberg Confirms R-Rating, Says It's a Violent, \"Different Wolverine\"|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=May 9, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe film included some vintage [[X-Men]] comic books, used both to advance the plot and as a [[metafiction]]al reference. The director clarified that Marvel Comics allowed this on the condition that they could use actual characters and designs, but not use any real comic book issues. As a result, the comic book covers and pages seen in the film were made specifically for it, by writer [[Joe Quesada]] and artist [[Dan Panosian]]. Mangold commented that \"The reality was that, like in Unforgiven, when [Clint] Eastwood runs into Richard Harris, who\u2019s writing these fictional accounts of the great Western heroes, or Pat Garrett in Billy the Kid, where you\u2019ve got these aging heroes who kind of are twilight versions of their own legends \u2014 I think that idea, of being a kind of celebrity, or like a sports star long past your heyday, was really interesting for me to investigate with this kind of world.\"<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.slashfilm.com/interview-logan-director-james-mangold/|title= Interview: 'Logan' Director James Mangold on His Influences, PG-13 Violence, and the Political Relevance of the X-Men|author= Angie Han|date= February 16, 2017|publisher= Slash Film|accessdate=July 30, 2019}}</ref> Panosian made 10 fake comic book covers, and interior arts were unused. He pointed that the arts had to resemble the style used in the 1980s, and pointed that they also served to contrast their campy style with the darker tone of the live-action film itself. He said that \"The colors and art itself juxtaposed against the raw and savage world in the film capture just how much innocence has been lost over time\".<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.theverge.com/2017/3/6/14821492/logan-x-men-comic-books-wolverine|title= The story behind the custom X-Men comics in Logan|author= Andrew Liptak|date= March 6, 2017|website= The Verge|accessdate=July 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\n[[File:Royal Street, New Orleans during French Quarter Festival.JPG|200px|left|thumbnail|Principal photography for ''Logan'' took place in New Orleans, Louisiana.]]\nOn March 5, 2015, James Mangold anticipated that filming would begin \"early next year.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://whatculture.com/film/wolverine-3-starts-filming-in-early-2016|title=Wolverine 3 Starts Filming In Early 2016|last=Connelly|first=Brendon|work=WhatCulture|date=March 5, 2015|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/mang0ld/status/573359978406232066|title=Filming begins early 2016|last=Mangold|first=James|work=[[Twitter]]|date=March 5, 2015|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> Prior to filming, the film was given the [[working title|false title]] of ''Juarez'' to lower the visibility of production, but the local media eventually uncovered the ruse.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.productionweekly.com/production-weekly-issue-983-thursday-february-25-2016-202-listings-44-pages/|title=PRODUCTION WEEKLY \u2013 ISSUE 983 \u2013 THURSDAY, FEBRUARY 25, 2016 / 202 LISTINGS \u2013 44 PAGES|last=Production Weekly Editors|work=Production Weekly|date=February 24, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113120637/https://www.productionweekly.com/production-weekly-issue-983-thursday-february-25-2016-202-listings-44-pages/|archivedate=November 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.projectcasting.com/casting-calls-acting-auditions/juarez-fox-casting|title=Fox's New Series 'Juarez' New Orleans Open Casting Call|last=Project Casting Editors|work=Project Casting|date=March 10, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmneworleans.org/for-the-local-community/filmed-in-new-orleans/filmography/|title=Filmography|last=New Orleans Editors|work=New Orleans|date=March 1, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107184132/http://www.filmneworleans.org/for-the-local-community/filmed-in-new-orleans/filmography|archive-date=November 7, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailysuperhero.com/2016/05/wolverine-3-secretly-started-filming-in.html|title=WOLVERINE 3 Secretly Started Filming in New Orleans Last Week Under the Code Name 'Juarez'|last=Daily SuperHero Editors|work=Daily SuperHero|date=May 8, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> On March 1, 2016, ''[[The Times-Picayune]]'' had confirmed that Mangold's film is preparing to shoot in [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]], with a starting schedule of May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nola.com/movies/index.ssf/2016/03/hugh_jackman_wolverine_3_new_orleans.html|title=Hugh Jackman's 'Wolverine 3' appears headed for a New Orleans shoot this May|last=Scott|first=Mike|work=[[The Times-Picayune]]|date=March 1, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> Producers Kinberg, Shuler Donner and Parker chose to film in Louisiana because of its popularity in film making locations,<ref name=Location/> as well as its [[Movie production incentives in the United States|filming incentive]], which includes a 40% tax credit for movie productions, though it requires a minimum expenditure of US$300,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.opportunitylouisiana.com/incentives/motion-picture-investor-tax-credit|title=MOTION PICTURE TAX CREDIT|last=Opportunity Louisiana Editors|work=Opportunity Louisiana|date=May 8, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> [[Principal photography]] was confirmed to have begun in New Orleans, with an original shooting schedule occurring from April 25 to August 13, 2016,<ref name=Location>{{cite web|url=http://www.thelocationguide.com/blog/2016/02/third-wolverine-film-to-be-shot-in-new-orleans-and-new-mexico/|title=Third Wolverine film to be shot in New Orleans and New Mexico|last=Deehan|first=Tom|work=The Location Guide|date=February 3, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113041020/http://www.thelocationguide.com/blog/2016/02/third-wolverine-film-to-be-shot-in-new-orleans-and-new-mexico/|archivedate=November 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://movieweb.com/wolverine-3-production-start-date-r-rated/|title=Wolverine 3 Begins Shooting, Will Be R-Rated|last=Gallagher|first=Brian|work=[[MovieWeb]]|date=May 9, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ramascreen.com/start-dates-and-filming-locations-for-xxx3-wolverine-3-avatar-2-and-more/|title=Start Dates And Filming Locations For xXx3, WOLVERINE 3, AVATAR 2, And More|last=Rama|work=Rama's Screen|date=February 1, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> albeit shooting was altered to start on May 2, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://heroichollywood.com/wolverine-3-starts-production/|title=Production Has Kicked Off On James Mangold's Sequel To 'The Wolverine'|last=Madden|first=Shawn|work=Action News 17|date=May 8, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn May 23, 2016, filming took place at the [[Michoud Assembly Facility|NASA Michoud Plant]] in [[Eastern New Orleans|New Orleans East]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nola.com/movies/index.ssf/2016/03/hugh_jackman_wolverine_3_new_orleans.html|title=Hugh Jackman is shooting 'Wolverine 3\u2032 at one of New Orleans' most popular filming locations|last=Christine|work=On Location Vacations|date=May 26, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> with Jackman being spotted, not far from [[Slidell, Louisiana|Slidell]], shooting a fight scene outdoors on the property.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sunherald.com/entertainment/movies-news-reviews/article79383562.html|title=Hugh Jackman spotted filming for Wolverine 3 at NASA's Michoud plant|last=Nelson|first=Karen|work=[[Sun Herald]]|date=May 23, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> On May 26, 2016, the intersection of [[Louisiana Highway 16|LA 16]] at [[U.S. Route 51 in Louisiana|US 51]] was closed for a time due to filming, with local store fronts don faux signage to transform [[Amite City, Louisiana|Amite City]], and east of Amite near Bell Road.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hammondstar.com/news/above-ground/article_32683387-7c52-5598-b481-9e2770287b5d.html|title=Hollywood production makes use of Hammond|last=Rester|first=Jacob|work=The Hammond Star|date=May 28, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170510090505/http://www.hammondstar.com/news/above-ground/article_32683387-7c52-5598-b481-9e2770287b5d.html|archive-date=May 10, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was revealed that scenes were filmed prior in [[Husser, Louisiana|Husser]] on May 25, 2016, with a scheduled daytime shoot to occur at the Greenlawn Cemetery in [[Hammond, Louisiana|Hammond]] on May 27, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.actionnews17.com/news/intersection-of-la-16us-51-closed-for-movie-filming-thursday-1584055|title=INTERSECTION OF LA 16/US 51 CLOSED FOR MOVIE FILMING THURSDAY|last=Action News 17 Editors|work=Action News 17|date=May 26, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> Filming took place from June 9, 2016, until June 10, 2016, in New Orleans and [[Metairie, Louisiana|Metairie]], respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.2016auditions.com/casting-call-featured-extras-wolverine-3-new-orleans-louisiana/|title=Casting Call For Featured Extras in 'Wolverine 3'|last=John|work=2016 Auditions|date=June 7, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn June 1, 2016, it was confirmed that 20th Century Fox have applied to film exterior scenes for ''Juarez'' on [[Louisiana Highway 15]] between Ferriday and Clayton from June 12, 2016, up until June 16, 2016,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2016/06/08/find-wolverine-3-filming-june-12-16-louisiana/|title=Find out where 'Wolverine 3' is filming on June 12 \u2013 16 in Louisiana|last=Christine|work=On Location Vacations|date=June 1, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> at the Ferriday Plaza Shopping Center,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knoe.com/home/headlines/Parts-of-Wolverine-Sequel-set-to-be-filmed-in-Concordia-Parish-381830401.html|title=Parts of Wolverine Sequel set to be filmed in Concordia Parish|last=Loyacano|first=Kaitlyn|work=[[KNOE-TV]]|date=June 3, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> while a portion of [[U.S. Route 425]] between Ferriday and Clayton will be closed for a five-day period in connection with Fox's production.<ref name=Ferriday>{{cite web|url=http://www.hannapub.com/concordiasentinel/wolverine-sequel-filming-set-in-si-ferriday/article_105be8c8-2823-11e6-aea6-d7433f0fefa4.html|title=Wolverine sequel filming set in SI, Ferriday|last=Martin|first=Joey|work=The Concordia Sentinel|date=June 1, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.natchezdemocrat.com/2016/06/04/wolverine-filming-near-ferriday/|title='Wolverine' filming near Ferriday|last=Madden|first=Cain|work=The Concordia Sentinel|date=June 4, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> On June 1, 2016, ''The Concordia Sentinel'' revealed that Sicily Island High School and a house in [[Sicily Island, Louisiana|Sicily Island]] will be used in the production, while a crash scene will be shot on U.S. Route 425 just outside of Ferriday.<ref name=Ferriday/> Producers Kinberg, Shuler Donner and Parker choose to film in [[Ferriday, Louisiana]], because of [[Concordia Parish]]'s beautiful countryside and green cornfields.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hannapub.com/concordiasentinel/beautiful-country-cornfields-attracted-wolverine-producers-to-ferriday/article_c409b1ba-3328-11e6-b519-d7209cf60727.html|title='Beautiful country,' cornfields attracted Wolverine 3 producers to Ferriday|last=Martin|first=Joey|work=The Concordia Sentinel|date=June 15, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> On June 16, 2016, ''Juarez'' was originally scheduled to move on toward Sicily Island, however, additional periods of shooting were added.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.natchezdemocrat.com/2016/06/16/miss-lou-residents-get-excited-about-wolverine-filming-in-ferriday/|title=Miss-Lou residents get excited about 'Wolverine' filming in Ferriday|last=Madden|first=Cain|work=The Concordia Sentinel|date=June 15, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> [[Natchez, Mississippi]] had been chosen by producers of ''Juarez'' as the next filming location, for an upcoming scene which required the casting truck drivers,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beamovieextra.com/wolverine-3-currently-casting-extras/|title=Wolverine 3 Currently Casting Extras|last=Be a Movie Extra Editors|work=Be a Movie Extra|date=June 14, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> that will be filmed between June 14 up until June 28, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.projectcasting.com/casting-calls-acting-auditions/wolverine-3-mississippi-open-casting-call|title='Wolverine 3' Mississippi Open Casting Call|last=Project Casting Editors|work=Project Casting|date=June 6, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn July 12, 2016, the ''[[Albuquerque Journal]]'' confirmed that ''Juarez'' would move on to its third major filming location\u2014[[New Mexico]], which ran through August in [[Albuquerque, New Mexico|Albuquerque]], [[Rio Rancho, New Mexico|Rio Rancho]], [[Abiqui\u00fa, New Mexico|Abiqui\u00fa]], [[Tierra Amarilla, New Mexico|Tierra Amarilla]] and [[Chama, New Mexico|Chama]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abqjournal.com/806633/hugh-jackman-and-wolverine-to-film-in-nm.html|title=Hugh Jackman and 'Wolverine' to film in New Mexico|last=Gomez|first=Adrian|work=[[The Albuquerque Journal]]|date=June 12, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://santafetravelers.com/our-travels/stalking-hugh-jackman-new-mexico/|title=Stalking Hugh Jackman in New Mexico|last=Frank|first=Billie|work=Santa Fe Travelers|date=August 7, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref name=Mexico>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2016/07/28/wolverine-3-filming-moves-louisiana-new-mexico/|title='Wolverine 3' filming moves from Louisiana to New Mexico|last=Christine|work=On Location Vacations|date=July 28, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koat.com/article/latest-installment-of-wolverine-filming-in-new-mexico/5072147|title=Latest installment of 'Wolverine' filming in New Mexico|last=KOAT-TV Editors|work=[[KOAT-TV]]|date=June 13, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freeabq.com/2016/03/14/n-m-film-focus-seeing-being-stars/|title=N.M. Film Focus: Seeing, Being Stars|last=Valdez|first=Christa|work=ABQ Free Press|date=March 14, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113113908/http://www.freeabq.com/2016/03/14/n-m-film-focus-seeing-being-stars/|archive-date=November 13, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.santafenewmexican.com/news/blogs/neighbors/trailer-for-new-n-m--filmed-wolverine-movie-logan/article_e30b4b60-9a01-11e6-991d-1bde9688306c.html|title=Trailer for new N.M.-filmed Wolverine movie 'Logan' is here|last=Mitotero|first=El|work=[[The Santa Fe New Mexican]]|date=October 24, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> The New Mexico Film Office revealed that the production employed about 130 New Mexican crew members and two New Mexican cast members, as well as 600 extras throughout the production, the film office stated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecumenicalnews.com/article/wolverine-3-news-production-taking-place-in-new-mexico-until-august/47886.htm|title='Wolverine 3' production taking place in New Mexico until August|last=Cecille Ferrer|first=Socorro|work=[[Ecumenical News International]]|date=June 17, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> On July 17, 2016, it was reported that the production of ''Juarez'' was in the process of casting to work on a scene filmed on July 22, 2016, in Albuquerque, New Mexico.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.projectcasting.com/casting-calls-acting-auditions/wolverine-3-albuquerque-casting-call-nerds|title='Wolverine 3' Albuquerque Casting Call for Nerds|last=Project Casting Editors|work=Project Casting|date=July 17, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> On July 25, 2016, it was reported that filming had begun in the Northern Meadows neighborhood of Rio Rancho, while a few miles further down King Boulevard there is an elaborate set built with a toppled water tower,<ref name=Mexico/> that will be used for exterior shots until June 27, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://krqe.com/2016/07/25/wolverine-3-filming-exciting-for-most-in-rio-rancho-neighborhood/|title=\"Wolverine 3\" filming exciting for most in Rio Rancho neighborhood|last=Goldsmith|first=Alex|work=[[KRQE]]|date=July 25, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.projectcasting.com/casting-calls-acting-auditions/wolverine-3-albuquerque-casting-call-hispanic-soldiers|title='Wolverine 3' Albuquerque Casting Call for Hispanic Soldiers|last=Project Casting Editors|work=Project Casting|date=June 24, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> On August 11, 2016, it was reported that the production of ''Juarez'' were in the process of seeking worn out cars to work on an upcoming scene filmed on August 12, 2016, in Albuquerque, New Mexico.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.projectcasting.com/casting-calls-acting-auditions/hugh-jackmans-wolverine-3-albuquerque-casting-call-cars|title=Hugh Jackman's 'Wolverine 3' Albuquerque Casting Call for Cars|last=Project Casting Editors|work=Project Casting|date=August 11, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oneheadlightink.com/2016/08/11/todays-nm-film-fix-54/|title=Today's NM Film Fix|last=OneHeadlightInk Editors|work=OneHeadlightInk|date=August 11, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> Principal photography was confirmed to have ended in New Mexico on August 13, 2016,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movieweb.com/wolverine-3-wraps-new-mexico-hugh-hackman/|title=Wolverine 3 Wraps in New Mexico|last=Gallagher|first=Brian|work=[[MovieWeb]]|date=August 13, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2016/08/16/hugh-jackman-wraps-wolverine-3-new-mexico/|title=Hugh Jackman wraps up 'Wolverine 3' in New Mexico|last=Christine|work=On Location Vacations|date=August 16, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-3-hugh-jackman-video/|title=Watch: Hugh Jackman Celebrates the End of 'Wolverine 3' Filming with a Nice Shave|last=Romano|first=Nick|work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=August 20, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> with an altered shooting schedule occurring from May 2 to August 13, 2016,<ref name=Location/> while with [[post-production]] beginning subsequent to filming closure on August 23, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pro-labs.imdb.com/title/tt3315342|title=Logan (2017)|last=IMDb Editors|work=[[IMDb]]|date=September 12, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/lifestyle/family-relationships/wolverine-3-is-in-post-production/vp-AAiNvWe|title='Wolverine 3' Is In Post Production|last=MSN Editors|work=[[MSN]]|date=September 12, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/wolverine-3-logan-villain-revealed-boyd-holbrook/#images|title='Logan' Villain Revealed with First Image of Boyd Holbrook in the 'Wolverine' Sequel|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=October 10, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Post-production===\n[[File:Logan makeup and CGI.jpg|thumb|Hugh Jackman as Logan, with makeup and [[Computer-generated imagery|visual special effects.]]]]\n[[Film editing|Film editor]] [[Michael McCusker]] was finishing work on Mangold's ''Logan'', during the period of October 7, 2016, wherein he spoke of going through the dailies and breaking them down, and figuring out the structure of one scene which he described as a \"complicated, multi-component scene\".<ref name=Editor>{{cite web|url=http://www.provideocoalition.com/art-cut-michael-mccusker-ace-editor-girl-train/|title=ART OF THE CUT WITH MICHAEL MCCUSKER, ACE, EDITOR OF \"GIRL ON THE TRAIN\"|last=Hullfish|first=Steve|work=ProVideo Coalition|date=October 7, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> McCusker spoke of the task being rather time consuming, on the front end, albeit stating, \"I am looking at the back end experience with [Mangold] as the more important experience. I don't want to be searching for stuff for him, I want to be working towards getting the cut right.\"<ref name=Editor/> McCusker concluded by stating that another editor on ''Logan'' has use for post-production.<ref name=Editor/> Chas Jarrett was the overall visual effects supervisor and visual effects company [[Image Engine]] worked on most of the visual effects on ''Logan''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://image-engine.com/film/logan/|title=Logan |work=[[Image Engine]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://image-engine.com/film/logan/|title=LOGAN|last=Frei|first=Vincent|work=[[Image Engine]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chasjarrett.com/chasjarrett-projects|title=Projects|last=Jarrett|first=Chas|work=Chas Jarrett|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Music===\nIn July 2016, [[Cliff Martinez]] was announced as the composer of ''Logan'''s musical score.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehollywoodnews.com/2016/07/05/cliff-martinez-will-score-wolverine-3/|title=Cliff Martinez will score 'The Wolverine 3'|last=Heath|first=Paul|work=The Hollywood News|date=July 1, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.joblo.com/movie-news/composer-cliff-martinez-to-score-james-mangolds-untitled-wolverine-sequel-189|title=COMPOSER CLIFF MARTINEZ TO SCORE JAMES MANGOLD'S UNTITLED WOLVERINE SEQUEL|last=Shirey|first=Paul|publisher=[[Joblo.com]]|date=July 1, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2016/07/wolverine-3-hires-composer-cliff-martinez-score-marvel-1201702060/|title=Nicolas Winding Refn Favorite Cliff Martinez Will Score 'Wolverine 3'|last=Calvario|first=Liz|work=[[IndieWire]]|date=July 1, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2016/07/01/cliff-martinez-to-score-james-mangolds-wolverine-sequel/|title=Cliff Martinez to Score James Mangold's 'Wolverine' Sequel |work=Film Music Reporter|date=July 1, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> In December 2016, Mangold announced that [[Marco Beltrami]], who had previously collaborated with Mangold on ''[[3:10 to Yuma (2007 film)|3:10 to Yuma]]'' (2007) and ''[[The Wolverine (film)|The Wolverine]]'' (2013), would take over from Martinez and score ''Logan'' instead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2016/12/31/marco-beltrami-to-score-james-mangolds-logan/|title=Marco Beltrami to Score James Mangold's 'Logan' |work=Film Music Reporter|date=December 31, 2016|accessdate=January 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n;Track listing\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Logan (Official Motion Picture Soundtrack)\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Marco Beltrami]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = March 31, 2017\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film score]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=57|s=31}}\n| label      = [[Sony Classical]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = ''Logan (Original Motion Picture S