 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/logan-hugh-jackman-laura-movie-recasting-wolverine-1051147 |title='Logan' Team on Dreaming Up a 'Laura' Spinoff and Finding the Drama in Wolverine's Goodbye |first=Aaron |last=Couch |date=October 24, 2017 |access-date=December 30, 2018 |journal=[[Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> However few details other than Mangold and Craig Kyle's involvement had been released, nor was it ever listed on Fox's schedule.\n\nAfter [[Acquisition of 21st Century Fox by Disney|Disney's purchase of Fox]] was finalized in 2019, all ''X-Men'' films in development were cancelled, quelling any chances of an X-23 film.<ref name=\"XMenCanceled\">{{cite web | url = https://www.mirror.co.uk/film/x-men-fantastic-four-films-13852013 | title = X-Men and Fantastic Four films 'cancelled' at Fox after Disney acquisition | publisher =[[Daily Mirror]] | first = Lewis | last = Knight | date = January 13, 2019 | accessdate = January 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.foxmovies.com/movies/logan}}\n* {{IMDb title|3315342}}\n* {{Mojo title|wolverine2017|Logan}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|logan_2017|Logan}}\n* {{Metacritic film|logan-2017|Logan}}\n* {{AllMovie title|596219}}\n\n{{Wolverine}}\n{{X-Men media}}\n{{Marvel Comics films}}\n{{James Mangold}}\n\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s action films]]\n[[Category:2010s adventure films]]\n[[Category:2010s psychological drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s science fiction action films]]\n[[Category:2010s sequel films]]\n[[Category:2010s superhero films]]\n[[Category:20th Century Fox films]]\n[[Category:American action adventure films]]\n[[Category:American science fiction adventure films]]\n[[Category:American psychological drama films]]\n[[Category:American road movies]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:American superhero films]]\n[[Category:Americ