ia) Pte. Ltd.|isbn=978-0-470-82958-5}}.\n*{{Citation |last=Datta |first=Amaresh |title= The Encyclopaedia Of Indian Literature (Volume Two) (Devraj To Jyoti), Volume 2|year=2005|ref=harv|authorlink= |location=New Delhi |publisher=Sahitya Akademi|isbn=978-81-260-1194-0}}.\n*{{Citation |last=Fuller |first=Christopher John |title=The camphor flame: popular Hinduism and society in India |year=2004 |ref=harv|authorlink= |location=New Jersey |publisher=Princeton University Press |isbn=978-0-691-12048-5}}.\n*{{Citation |last=Harman |first=William P. |title= The sacred marriage of a Hindu goddess |year=1992|ref=harv|authorlink= |location=Delhi |publisher=Indiana University Press |isbn=978-1-59884-655-3}}.\n*{{Citation |title=History & description of Sri Meenakshi Temple |year=1987 |ref=harv|last1=Iyer |last2=T. R. |first1=T. G. S. Balaram |first2=Rajagopalan |authorlink= |location= |publisher=Sri Karthik Agency |isbn=}}.\n*{{Citation |last=Ki |first=Palaniyappan |title=The Great Temple of Madurai: English version of the book Koilmanagar |year=1963 |ref=harv|authorlink= |location= |publisher= |isbn=}}.\n*{{Citation |last=King |first=Anthony D. |title=Buildings and Society: Essays on the Social Development of the Built Environment|url=https://books.google.com/?id=1HtVU6D2LOUC&printsec=frontcover&dq=Buildings+and+Society:+Essays+on+the+Social+Development+of+the+Built+Environment#v=onepage&q=meenakshi&f=false|year=2005 |ref=harv|authorlink= |location= |publisher=Taylor & Francis e-library |isbn=978-0-203-48075-5}}.\n*{{Citation |last=Kinsley |first=David|title= Hindu goddesses: visions of the divine feminine in the Hindu religious tradition By David Kinsley|year=1998|ref=harv|authorlink= |location=Delhi |publisher=The Regents of the University of California|isbn=978-81-208-0394-7}}.\n*{{Citation |last=Knott |first=Kim |title=Hinduism: A Very Short Introduction |year=2000 |ref=harv|authorlink= |location=Oxford |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0192853875 }}.\n*{{Citat